    49)    ! PATCH TYPE: The following are arrays of cohorts that populate the current patch.      !
    50)    !             This is the lowest (most nested) part of the memory structure.            !
    51)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!  
    52)    type patchtype
    53)       !----- Number of cohorts in this patch.   This number can be zero (empty patch). ----!
    54)       integer :: ncohorts
    55)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!  
    56) 
    57) 
    58)       !----- Global index of the first cohort across all cohorts. -------------------------!
    59)       integer :: coglob_id
    60)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
    61) 
    62) 
    63) 
    64)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
    65)       ! Plant functional type.  Default values are:                                        !
    66)       ! PFT | Name                                     | Grass   | Tropical | agriculture? !
    67)       !-----+------------------------------------------+---------+----------+--------------!
    68)       !   1 | C4 grass                                 |     yes |      yes |          yes !
    69)       !   2 | Early tropical                           |      no |      yes |           no !
    70)       !   3 | Mid tropical                             |      no |      yes |           no !
    71)       !   4 | Late tropical                            |      no |      yes |           no !
    72)       !   5 | Temperate C3 grass                       |     yes |       no |          yes !
    73)       !   6 | Northern pines                           |      no |       no |           no !
    74)       !   7 | Southern pines                           |      no |       no |           no !
    75)       !   8 | Late conifers                            |      no |       no |           no !
    76)       !   9 | Early temperate deciduous                |      no |       no |           no !
    77)       !  10 | Mid temperate deciduous                  |      no |       no |           no !
    78)       !  11 | Late temperate deciduous                 |      no |       no |           no !
    79)       !  12 | C3 pasture                               |     yes |       no |          yes !
    80)       !  13 | C3 crop (e.g.,wheat, rice, soybean)      |     yes |       no |          yes !
    81)       !  14 | C4 pasture                               |     yes |      yes |          yes !
    82)       !  15 | C4 crop (e.g.,corn/maize)                |     yes |      yes |          yes !
    83)       !  16 | Tropical C3 grass                        |     yes |      yes |          yes !
    84)       !  17 | Araucaria (based on 7, tropical allom.)  |      no |      yes |           no !
    85)       !-----+------------------------------------------+---------+----------+--------------!
    86)       integer ,pointer,dimension(:) :: pft
    87) 
    88)       ! Density of plants (number/m2)
    89)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: nplant
    90) 
    91)       ! phenology_status codes:
    92)       !  0 - plant has the maximum LAI, given its size
    93)       !  1 - plant is growing leaves
    94)       ! -1 - plant is actively dropping leaves
    95)       !  2 - plant has no leaves
    96)       integer ,pointer,dimension(:) :: phenology_status
    97) 
    98)       ! recruit_dbh codes (updated every month):
    99)       ! 0 - new plant
   100)       ! 1 - first month with DBH > 10cm
   101)       ! 2 - established as DBH > 10cm
   102)       integer, pointer, dimension(:) :: recruit_dbh
   103) 
   104)       ! census_status codes (updated every census):
   105)       ! 0 - this cohort has never been with DBH > 10 cm at census times
   106)       ! 1 - New recruit (DBH > 10 cm for the first census)
   107)       ! 2 - Established (DBH > 10 cm for at least two censuses
   108)       integer, pointer, dimension(:) :: census_status
   109) 
   110)       ! Plant height (m)
   111)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: hite
   112) 
   113)       ! Above-ground biomass (kgC/plant)
   114)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: agb
   115) 
   116)       ! Basal area (cm2)
   117)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: basarea
   118)      
   119)       ! Rate of change in agb (kgC/plant/yr)
   120)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: dagb_dt
   121)      
   122)       ! Rate of change in agb (1/yr)
   123)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: dlnagb_dt
   124)      
   125)       ! Rate of change in basal area (cm2/yr)
   126)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: dba_dt
   127)      
   128)       ! Rate of change in basal area (1/yr)
   129)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: dlnba_dt
   130)      
   131)       ! Rate of change in dbh (cm/yr)
   132)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: ddbh_dt
   133)      
   134)       ! Rate of change in dbh ( 1/yr)
   135)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: dlndbh_dt
   136) 
   137)       ! Plant diameter at breast height (cm)
   138)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: dbh
   139) 
   140)       ! Biomass of the structural wood (kgC/plant)
   141)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: bdead
   142) 
   143)       ! Biomass of leaves (kgC/plant)
   144)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: bleaf
   145) 
   146)       ! Biomass of live tissue (kgC/plant)
   147)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: balive
   148) 
   149)       ! Biomass of fine roots (kgC/plant)
   150)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: broot
   151) 
   152)       ! Biomass of sapwood above ground (kgC/plant)
   153)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: bsapwooda
   154) 
   155)       ! Biomass of sapwood below ground (kgC/plant)
   156)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: bsapwoodb
   157) 
   158)       ! Plant storage pool of carbon [kgC/plant]
   159)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: bstorage
   160) 
   161)       ! Amount of seeds produced for dispersal [kgC/plant]
   162)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: bseeds
   163) 
   164)       ! Leaf area index (m2 leaf / m2 ground)
   165)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lai
   166) 
   167)       ! Wood area index (m2 wood / m2 ground)
   168)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wai
   169) 
   170)       ! Crown area (m2 crown / m2 ground)
   171)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: crown_area
   172) 
   173)       ! Logical test to check whether the cohort leaves can be resolved...
   174)       logical, pointer, dimension(:) :: leaf_resolvable
   175)       logical, pointer, dimension(:) :: wood_resolvable
   176)      
   177)       ! Monthly carbon balance for past 12 months and the current month
   178)       ! (kgC/plant) - 13th column holds the partial month integration
   179)       real, pointer,dimension(:,:) :: cb           !(13,ncohorts)
   180) 
   181)       ! Maximum monthly carbon balance for past 12 months and the current 
   182)       ! month  if cohort were at the top of the canopy (maximum light).
   183)       ! (kgC/plant) - 13th column holds the partial month integration.
   184)       real, pointer,dimension(:,:) :: cb_lightmax  !(13,ncohorts)
   185) 
   186)       ! Maximum monthly carbon balance for past 12 months and the current 
   187)       ! month  if cohort had access to all soil moisture needed (maximum moisture/fsw).
   188)       ! (kgC/plant) - 13th column holds the partial month integration.
   189)       real, pointer,dimension(:,:) :: cb_moistmax  !(13,ncohorts)
   190) 
   191)       ! Maximum monthly carbon balance for past 12 months and the current 
   192)       ! month  if cohort had access to all soil moisture needed (maximum moisture/fsw)
   193)       ! AND the cohort was at the top of the canopy (maximum light).
   194)       ! (kgC/plant) - 13th column holds the partial month integration.
   195)       real, pointer,dimension(:,:) :: cb_mlmax  !(13,ncohorts)
   196) 
   197)       ! Relative carbon balance:
   198)       !                    1         CB_lightmax             CB_watermax 
   199)       !                  ----   = k ------------- + (1 - k) -------------
   200)       !                   CR             CB                      CB      
   201)       ! k is the ddmort_const given on the namelist
   202)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: cbr_bar
   203) 
   204)       ! Leaf internal energy (J/m2 ground)
   205)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_energy
   206) 
   207)       ! Leaf temperature (K)
   208)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_temp
   209) 
   210)       ! Leaf vapour pressure deficit (Pa)
   211)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_vpdef
   212) 
   213)       ! Leaf temperature of the previous step (K)
   214)       real, pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_temp_pv
   215) 
   216)       ! Fraction of liquid water on top of leaves (dimensionless)
   217)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_fliq
   218) 
   219)       ! Leaf surface water (kg/m2 ground)
   220)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_water
   221) 
   222)       ! Leaf heat capacity [ J/m2/K]
   223)       real, pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_hcap
   224) 
   225)       ! Wood internal energy (J/m2 ground)
   226)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_energy
   227) 
   228)       ! Wood temperature (K)
   229)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_temp
   230) 
   231)       ! Wood temperature at previous step(K)
   232)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_temp_pv
   233) 
   234)       ! Fraction of liquid water on top of wood (dimensionless)
   235)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_fliq
   236) 
   237)       ! Wood surface water (kg/m2 ground)
   238)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_water
   239) 
   240)       ! Wood heat capacity [ J/m2/K]
   241)       real, pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_hcap
   242) 
   243)       ! Reduced wind at the cohort level (m/s)
   244)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: veg_wind
   245) 
   246)       ! Leaf surface specific humidity for open stomata (kg/kg)
   247)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lsfc_shv_open
   248) 
   249)       ! Leaf surface specific humidity for closed stomata (kg/kg)
   250)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lsfc_shv_closed
   251) 
   252)       ! Leaf surface CO2 for open stomata (�mol/mol)
   253)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lsfc_co2_open
   254) 
   255)       ! Leaf surface CO2 for closed stomata (�mol/mol)
   256)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lsfc_co2_closed
   257) 
   258)       ! Leaf interecellular specific humidity (kg/kg)
   259)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lint_shv
   260) 
   261)       ! Leaf intercellular CO2 for open stomata (�mol/mol)
   262)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lint_co2_open
   263) 
   264)       ! Leaf intercellular CO2 for closed stomata (�mol/mol)
   265)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: lint_co2_closed
   266)

   268)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   269)       !     The following variables are used for growth rates.  They are for internal use  !
   270)       ! only and are meaningless in the output files (they saved only in HISTORY).         !
   271)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   272)       ! Mean leaf respiration rate (umol/m2 ground/s), averaged over 1 day
   273)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_leaf_resp
   274)       ! Mean root respiration rate (umol/m2 ground/s), averaged over 1 day
   275)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_root_resp
   276)       ! Gross primary productivity (GPP) [umol/m2 ground/s], averaged over 1 day
   277)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_gpp
   278)       ! Potential GPP in the absence of N limitation [umol/m2 ground/s],
   279)       ! averaged over 1 day
   280)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_gpp_pot
   281)       ! Maximum GPP if cohort were at the top of the canopy (maximum light)
   282)       ! [umol/m2 ground/s], averaged over 1 day
   283)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_gpp_lightmax
   284)       ! Maximum GPP if cohort had all soil moisture needed (maximum soil moisture)
   285)       ! [umol/m2 ground/s], averaged over 1 day
   286)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_gpp_moistmax
   287)       ! Maximum GPP if cohort had maximum soil moisture and maximum light
   288)       ! [umol/m2 ground/s], averaged over 1 day
   289)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_gpp_mlmax
   290) 
   291) 
   292)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppleaf
   293)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppfroot
   294)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppsapwood
   295)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppcroot
   296)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppseeds
   297)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppwood
   298)       real,pointer,dimension(:) :: today_nppdaily
   299)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   300)

   303)       ! Plant growth respiration (kgC/plant/day)
   304)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_growth_resp

   306)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: root_growth_resp
   307)       ! Plant growth respiration (kgC/plant/day)

   315)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: sapb_storage_resp

   322) 
   323)       ! Mortality rate [yr-1]
   324)       real , pointer, dimension(:,:) :: mort_rate
   325) 
   326)       ! This specifies the index of the deepest soil layer of which the 
   327)       ! cohort can access water.
   328)       integer ,pointer,dimension(:) :: krdepth
   329) 
   330)       ! The model reports annual growth, mortality, cut and recruitment.  
   331)       ! These rates are calculated with respect to two censuses.  This 
   332)       ! is the flag specifying if a cohort was present at the first
   333)       ! census.
   334)       integer ,pointer,dimension(:) :: first_census
   335) 
   336)       ! Flag specifying if this cohort is a new recruit with respect
   337)       ! to the first census.
   338)       integer ,pointer,dimension(:) :: new_recruit_flag
   339) 
   340)       ! Light level received by this cohort, its diurnal and monthly means
   341)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: light_level
   342)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: light_level_beam
   343)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: light_level_diff
   344) 
   345)       ! PAR flux density centered on cohort, diurnal and monthly means
   346)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: par_level_beam    ! beam
   347)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: par_level_diffu   ! diffuse down
   348)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: par_level_diffd   ! diffuse up
   349) 
   350)       ! Photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) absorbed by the 
   351)       ! cohort leaves(units are W/m2)
   352)       real ,pointer,dimension(:)   :: par_l
   353) 
   354)       ! Photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) absorbed by the 
   355)       ! cohort leaves (units are W/m2), beam component
   356)       real ,pointer,dimension(:)   :: par_l_beam
   357) 
   358)       ! Photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) absorbed by the 
   359)       ! cohort leaves (units are W/m2), diffuse component
   360)       real ,pointer,dimension(:)   :: par_l_diffuse
   361) 
   362)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort leaves, W/m2
   363)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_l
   364) 
   365)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort leaves, W/m2, beam component
   366)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_l_beam
   367) 
   368)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort leaves, W/m2, diffuse 
   369)       ! component
   370)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_l_diffuse
   371) 
   372)       ! Total long wave radiation absorbed by the cohort leaves (W/m2)
   373)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rlong_l
   374) 
   375)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort wood, W/m2
   376)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_w
   377) 
   378)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort wood, W/m2, beam component
   379)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_w_beam
   380) 
   381)       ! Total short wave radiation absorbed by the cohort wood, W/m2, diffuse 
   382)       ! component
   383)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rshort_w_diffuse
   384) 
   385)       ! Total long wave radiation absorbed by the cohort wood (W/m2)
   386)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: rlong_w
   387) 
   388)       !----- Radiation profile for this patch, at thhe cohort interfaces (W/m2). ----------!
   389)       !  1. PAR, Beam, Down                                                                !
   390)       !  2. PAR, Beam, Up (only Medvigy's radiation, zero for others).                     !
   391)       !  3. PAR, Diff, Down                                                                !
   392)       !  4. PAR, Diff, Up                                                                  !
   393)       !  5. NIR, Beam, Down                                                                !
   394)       !  6. NIR, Beam, Up (only Medvigy's radiation, zero for others).                     !
   395)       !  7. NIR, Diff, Down                                                                !
   396)       !  8. NIR, Diff, Up                                                                  !
   397)       !  9. TIR, Diff, Down                                                                !
   398)       ! 10. TIR. Diff, Up                                                                  !
   399)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   400)       real ,pointer,dimension(:,:) :: rad_profile
   401) 
   402)       ! Leaf boundary layer conductance for heat/entropy  [J/K/m2leaf/s]
   403)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_gbh
   404) 
   405)       ! Leaf boundary layer conductance for water [kg/m2leaf/s]
   406)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_gbw

   409)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_gbh

   411)       ! Wood boundary layer conductance for water [kg/m2wood/s]
   412)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: wood_gbw

   418)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: A_closed

   421)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: A_light

   425)

   430)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: psi_open

   434)

   436)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: gsw_open
   437)

   439)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: gsw_closed
   440)

   442)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_gsw

   445)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: fsw

   448)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: fsn
   449)

   451)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: fs_open
   452) 
   453)       ! Water supply (kg_H2O/m2/s)
   454)       real , pointer, dimension(:) :: water_supply
   455)

   457)       ! roots [kgC/plant]
   458)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: leaf_maintenance
   459)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: root_maintenance
   460)      
   461)       ! Leaf loss to litter layer due to phenology [kgC/plant]
   462)       real , pointer, dimension(:) :: leaf_drop
   463)

   466)       real ,pointer,dimension(:) :: root_respiration

   468)       ! Gross Primary Productivity [umol/m2/s]
   469)       real, pointer,dimension(:) :: gpp

   477)       ! Phenology-related
   478)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: turnover_amp
   479)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: llspan

   481)       real, pointer, dimension(:) :: sla
   482) 
   483)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   484)       ! These are diagnostic variables, averaged over various time scales.                 !
   485)       ! FMEAN -- averaged over FRQSUM (the least between FRQFAST, FRQSTATE and one day).   !
   486)       ! DMEAN -- daily averages                                                            !
   487)       ! MMEAN -- monthly averages                                                          !
   488)       ! MMSQU -- monthly mean sum of squares                                               !
   489)       ! QMEAN -- mean diel                                                                 !
   490)       ! QMSQU -- mean diel (mean sum of squares)                                           !
   491)       !                                                                                    !
   492)       ! pl means plant              (intensive variable)                                   !
   493)       ! m2l means m2 of leaf area   (intensive variable)                                   !
   494)       ! m2g means m2 of ground area (extensive variable)                                   !
   495)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   496)       !----- Fast averages. ---------------------------------------------------------------!
   497)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_gpp              ! Gross prim. prod. [ kgC/pl/yr]
   498)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_npp              ! Net primary prod. [ kgC/pl/yr]
   499)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_leaf_resp        ! Leaf respiration  [ kgC/pl/yr]
   500)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_root_resp        ! Root respiration  [ kgC/pl/yr]
   501)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_leaf_growth_resp ! Growth resp.      [ kgC/pl/yr]
   502)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_root_growth_resp ! Growth resp.      [ kgC/pl/yr]
   503)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_sapa_growth_resp ! Growth resp.      [ kgC/pl/yr]
   504)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_sapb_growth_resp ! Growth resp.      [ kgC/pl/yr]

   812)    ! SITE TYPE:  The following are the patch level arrays that populate the current site.  !

   823)       !  PACO_ID -- The global index of the first cohort in all patches                    !
   824)       !  PACO_N  -- The number of cohorts in each patch                                    !
   825)       !  PAGLOB_ID -- Global index of the first patch in this vector, across all patches.  !
   826)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
   827)       integer,pointer,dimension(:) :: paco_id
   828)       integer,pointer,dimension(:) :: paco_n
   829)       integer :: paglob_id

   831)

   838) 
   839)

   853)       !  AREA      -- patch area (relative to the total SITE area).                        !
   854)       !  AGE       -- time since last disturbance (years)                                  !
   855)       !  DIST_TYPE -- patch type                                                           !
   856)       !               1.  Clear cut (cropland and pasture).                                !
   857)       !               2.  Forest plantation.                                               !
   858)       !               3.  Tree fall.                                                       !
   859)       !               4.  Fire.                                                            !
   860)       !               5.  Forest regrowth.                                                 !
   861)       !               6.  Logged forest.                                                   !
   862)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!

  1031)       ! budget, and will compute what enters, what stays, and what leaves ED. !

  1033)       ! time for all fluxes, and the total storage at the beginning of the    !
  1034)       ! next time step (or the final storage between the previous analysis    !
  1035)       ! and this one).                                                        !

  1299)       !====================================================================================!
  1300)       !====================================================================================!
  1301)       !     Patch-level diagnostic variables:  these are either fluxes or state variables, !
  1302)       ! averaged over different scales, for each patch.                                    !
  1303)       !                                                                                    !
  1304)       !   FMEAN -- average over one frqsum time interval (usually sub-daily)               !
  1305)       !   DMEAN -- daily mean                                                              !
  1306)       !   MMEAN -- monthly mean                                                            !
  1307)       !   MMSQU -- monthly mean sum of squares                                             !
  1308)       !   QMEAN -- mean diel                                                               !
  1309)       !   QMSQU -- mean sum of squares for the diel                                        !
  1310)       !                                                                                    !
  1311)       !   Acronyms used in the description below:                                          !
  1312)       !   ATM       -- air above canopy                                                    !
  1313)       !   CAS       -- canopy air space                                                    !
  1314)       !   TSPL      -- temporary snow/pounding layer                                       !
  1315)       !   PAR       -- photosynthetically active radiation                                 !
  1316)       !   NIR       -- near infra-red                                                      !
  1317)       !   SW        -- short wave                                                          !
  1318)       !   LW        -- long wave                                                           !
  1319)       !   VPD       -- Vapour pressure deficit                                             !
  1320)       !   Theta_Eiv -- ice vapour equivalent potential temperature                         !
  1321)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  1322)       !----- Photosynthesis/Decomposition. ------------------------------------------------!
  1323)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_rh              ! Heterotr. resp.    [umol/m2/s]
  1324)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_cwd_rh          ! CWD respiration    [umol/m2/s]
  1325)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_nep             ! Net Ecosyst. Prod. [umol/m2/s]
  1326)       !----- State variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  1327)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_rk4step         ! RK4 time step      [        s]
  1328)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_available_water ! Available water    [    kg/m2]
  1329)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_theiv       ! CAS Theta_Eiv      [        K]
  1330)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_theta       ! CAS Potential temp.[        K]
  1331)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_vpdef       ! CAS Vap. Pres. Def.[       Pa]
  1332)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_temp        ! CAS Temperature    [        K]
  1333)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_shv         ! CAS Specific hum.  [    kg/kg]
  1334)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_co2         ! CAS CO2 mix. ratio [ umol/mol]
  1335)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_rhos        ! CAS air density    [    kg/m3]
  1336)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_can_prss        ! CAS pressure       [       Pa]
  1337)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_gnd_temp        ! Ground temperature [        K]
  1338)       real,pointer,dimension(:)   :: fmean_gnd_shv         ! Ground spec. hum.  [    kg/kg]

  1673)       !     Soil properties.                                                               !
  1674)       ! LSL        -- Index of the lowest soil layer (simulation dependent).
  1675)       !                                                                                    !
  1676)       ! NCOL_SOIL  -- Index of the soil colour class (used to find the ground albedo)
  1677)       !       |-----------------------------------------------------------------------|    !
  1678)       !       |       |   Dry soil  |  Saturated  |       |   Dry soil  |  Saturated  |    !
  1679)       !       | Class |-------------+-------------| Class +-------------+-------------|    !
  1680)       !       |       |  VIS |  NIR |  VIS |  NIR |       |  VIS |  NIR |  VIS |  NIR |    !
  1681)       !       |-------+------+------+------+------+-------+------+------+------+------|    !
  1682)       !       |     1 | 0.36 | 0.61 | 0.25 | 0.50 |    11 | 0.24 | 0.37 | 0.13 | 0.26 |    !
  1683)       !       |     2 | 0.34 | 0.57 | 0.23 | 0.46 |    12 | 0.23 | 0.35 | 0.12 | 0.24 |    !
  1684)       !       |     3 | 0.32 | 0.53 | 0.21 | 0.42 |    13 | 0.22 | 0.33 | 0.11 | 0.22 |    !
  1685)       !       |     4 | 0.31 | 0.51 | 0.20 | 0.40 |    14 | 0.20 | 0.31 | 0.10 | 0.20 |    !
  1686)       !       |     5 | 0.30 | 0.49 | 0.19 | 0.38 |    15 | 0.18 | 0.29 | 0.09 | 0.18 |    !
  1687)       !       |     6 | 0.29 | 0.48 | 0.18 | 0.36 |    16 | 0.16 | 0.27 | 0.08 | 0.16 |    !
  1688)       !       |     7 | 0.28 | 0.45 | 0.17 | 0.34 |    17 | 0.14 | 0.25 | 0.07 | 0.14 |    !
  1689)       !       |     8 | 0.27 | 0.43 | 0.16 | 0.32 |    18 | 0.12 | 0.23 | 0.06 | 0.12 |    !
  1690)       !       |     9 | 0.26 | 0.41 | 0.15 | 0.30 |    19 | 0.10 | 0.21 | 0.05 | 0.10 |    !
  1691)       !       |    10 | 0.25 | 0.39 | 0.14 | 0.28 |    20 | 0.08 | 0.16 | 0.04 | 0.08 |    !
  1692)       !       |-----------------------------------------------------------------------|    !
  1693)       !                                                                                    !
  1694)       !   Soil type 21 is a special case in which we use the albedo method that used to be !
  1695)       ! the default in ED-2.1.                                                             !
  1696)       !                                                                                    !
  1697)       !                                                                                    !
  1698)       ! NTEXT_SOIL -- Index of the soil texture class, similar to the USDA classification  !
  1699)       !               except that clay is split into four classes (11,15,16,17).           !
  1700)       !                                                                                    !
  1701)       !   1 -- sand                |   7 -- silty clay loam     |  13 -- bedrock           !
  1702)       !   2 -- loamy sand          |   8 -- clayey loam         |  14 -- silt              !
  1703)       !   3 -- sandy loam          |   9 -- sandy clay          |  15 -- heavy clay        !
  1704)       !   4 -- silt loam           |  10 -- silty clay          |  16 -- clayey sand       !
  1705)       !   5 -- loam                |  11 -- clay                |  17 -- clayey silt       !
  1706)       !   6 -- sandy clay loam     |  12 -- peat                                           !
  1707)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  1708)       integer,pointer,dimension(:)   :: lsl
  1709)       integer,pointer,dimension(:)   :: ncol_soil

  2170)       ! The matrix is arranged as follows (LAI,VARIABLE,POLYGON)

  2176)       !====================================================================================!
  2177)       !====================================================================================!
  2178)       !     Polygon-level diagnostic variables:  these are either fluxes or state          !
  2179)       ! variables, averaged over different time scales, for each polygon.  They are in the !
  2180)       ! output for convenience only.  Most came from the nested dimensions (sites, patches !
  2181)       ! and cohorts).                                                                      !
  2182)       !                                                                                    !
  2183)       !   FMEAN -- average over one frqsum time interval (usually sub-daily)               !
  2184)       !   DMEAN -- daily mean                                                              !
  2185)       !   MMEAN -- monthly mean                                                            !
  2186)       !   MMSQU -- monthly mean sum of squares                                             !
  2187)       !   QMEAN -- mean diel                                                               !
  2188)       !   QMSQU -- mean sum of squares for the diel                                        !
  2189)       !                                                                                    !
  2190)       !   Acronyms used in the description below:                                          !
  2191)       !   ATM       -- air above canopy                                                    !
  2192)       !   CAS       -- canopy air space                                                    !
  2193)       !   TSPL      -- temporary snow/pounding layer                                       !
  2194)       !   PAR       -- photosynthetically active radiation                                 !
  2195)       !   NIR       -- near infra-red                                                      !
  2196)       !   SW        -- short wave                                                          !
  2197)       !   LW        -- long wave                                                           !
  2198)       !   VPD       -- Vapour pressure deficit                                             !
  2199)       !   Theta_Eiv -- ice vapour equivalent potential temperature                         !
  2200) 
  2201)

  2830)    !=======================================================================================!
  2831)    !=======================================================================================!
  2832) 
  2833) 
  2834) 
  2835) 
  2836) 
  2837) 
  2838)    !=======================================================================================!
  2839)    !=======================================================================================!
  2840)    !  GLOBAL VARIABLES -- These variables are allocated and assigned before the parallel   !
  2841)    !                      distribution, so we don't want to keep it inside the structure.  !
  2842)    !                      In case of serial runs, we should have offset full of zeroes and !
  2843)    !                      the polygons numbered from 1 to the number of polygons.  In a    !
  2844)    !                      non-POI parallel run, we want to allocate "mpolygons" in each    !
  2845)    !                      node, but then must keep track of the actual polygon "ID" to     !
  2846)    !                      write the output correctly.                                      !
  2847)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2848)    ! Number of polygons in each grid, for each machine. so this has a ngrids size. 
  2849)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: gdpy
  2850) 
  2851)    ! Number of sites in each grid, for each machine.
  2852)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: gdsi
  2853) 
  2854)    ! Number of patches in each grid, for each machine.
  2855)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: gdpa
  2856) 
  2857)    ! Number of cohorts in each grid, for each machine.
  2858)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: gdco
  2859)   
  2860) 
  2861)    ! Offset for each machine, so this has a nmachs size.
  2862)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: py_off 
  2863)   
  2864)    ! Offset for each machine, so this has a nmachs size.
  2865)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: si_off 
  2866) 
  2867)    ! Offset for each machine, so this has a nmachs size.
  2868)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: pa_off 
  2869) 
  2870)    ! Offset for each machine, so this has a nmachs size.
  2871)    integer, dimension(maxmach,maxgrds) :: co_off 
  2872) 
  2873) 
  2874)    type(edtype),pointer,dimension(:) :: edgrid_g
  2875) 
  2876)    ! The following are swap variables used during
  2877)    ! deallocation-reallocation
  2878) 
  2879)    type(edtype)      :: edswap_g
  2880) 
  2881)    type(polygontype) :: polyswap_g
  2882) 
  2883)    type(sitetype)    :: siteswap_g
  2884) 
  2885)    type(patchtype)   :: patchswap_g
  2886)   
  2887)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2888)    !   The following variables are for tracking the number of variables written in the     !
  2889)    ! output, this way we avoid having the same ID used twice.                              !
  2890)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2891)    integer :: nioglobal, niogrid, niopoly, niosite
  2892) 
  2893)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2894)    ! Logical switch that decides if the pointer tables for IO need to be updated
  2895)    ! The number and allocation of cohorts and patches dictates this, and they 
  2896)    ! change at a monthly frequency typically.
  2897)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2898)    logical :: filltables
  2899)    !=======================================================================================!
  2900)    !=======================================================================================!
  2901) 
  2902) 
  2903)    contains
  2904) 
  2905) 
  2906) 
  2907)    !=======================================================================================!
  2908)    !=======================================================================================!
  2909)    !      This sub-routine allocates the global dimensions (outside the structure).        !
  2910)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2911)    subroutine allocate_edglobals(ngrids)
  2912) 
  2913)       use ed_var_tables, only : num_var  & ! intent(in)
  2914)                               , vt_info  & ! intent(in)
  2915)                               , maxvars  ! ! intent(in)
  2916)       implicit none
  2917) 
  2918)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2919)       integer :: ngrids
  2920)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2921)       
  2922) 
  2923) 
  2924)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2925)       !      Check that the structure is free.                                             !
  2926)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2927)       if (associated(edgrid_g))  then
  2928)          call fatal_error('Attempt to allocate global dimensions again!'                   &
  2929)                          ,'allocate_edglobals','ed_state_vars.f90')
  2930)       else
  2931)          nullify (edgrid_g)
  2932)          allocate(edgrid_g(ngrids))
  2933)       end if
  2934)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2935) 
  2936) 
  2937) 
  2938)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2939)       !      Allocate the basic variable table structures.                                 !
  2940)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2941)       allocate(num_var(ngrids))
  2942)       num_var = 0
  2943)       
  2944)       allocate(vt_info(maxvars,ngrids))
  2945)       vt_info(:,:)%vector_allocated = .false.
  2946) 
  2947) 
  2948)       !----- Initialize the global offsets. -----------------------------------------------!
  2949)       edgrid_g(:)%mach_cohort_offset_index  = 0
  2950)       edgrid_g(:)%mach_patch_offset_index   = 0
  2951)       edgrid_g(:)%mach_site_offset_index    = 0
  2952)       edgrid_g(:)%mach_polygon_offset_index = 0
  2953)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2954) 
  2955) 
  2956)       return
  2957)    end subroutine allocate_edglobals
  2958)    !=======================================================================================!
  2959)    !=======================================================================================!
  2960) 
  2961) 
  2962) 
  2963) 
  2964) 
  2965) 
  2966) 
  2967)    !=======================================================================================!
  2968)    !=======================================================================================!
  2969)    !     This subroutine allocates the polygon-level variables.                            !
  2970)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2971)    subroutine allocate_edtype(cgrid,npolygons)
  2972)       implicit none
  2973) 
  2974)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2975)       type(edtype), target     :: cgrid
  2976)       integer     , intent(in) :: npolygons
  2977)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  2978)       integer                  :: max_sitep1
  2979)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2980) 
  2981) 
  2982)       !------ For site adjacency.---------------------------------------------------------!
  2983)       max_sitep1 = max_site + 1
  2984)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2985) 
  2986) 
  2987)       !----- Make sure that we nullify all pointers for a safe allocation. ----------------!
  2988)       call nullify_edtype(cgrid)
  2989)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2990) 
  2991)       !----- Define the number of polygons. -----------------------------------------------!
  2992)       cgrid%npolygons = npolygons
  2993)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2994) 
  2995) 
  2996)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  2997)       !       There may be empty grids.  It never happens in the offline runs, but it is   !
  2998)       ! common in coupled model settings: some nodes may receive areas exclusively over    !
  2999)       ! oceans, and npolygons will be 0 in these nodes.  In this case, we should not       !
  3000)       ! attempt to allocate anything.                                                      !
  3001)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3002)       if (npolygons == 0) return
  3003)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3004) 
  3005)       allocate(cgrid%polygon                                        (npolygons))
  3006) 
  3007)

  3012)       allocate(cgrid%lat                        (                    npolygons))

  3014)       allocate(cgrid%yatm                       (                    npolygons))

  3016)       allocate(cgrid%wbar                       (                    npolygons))
  3017)       allocate(cgrid%Te                         (                    npolygons))
  3018)       allocate(cgrid%zbar                       (                    npolygons))
  3019)       allocate(cgrid%sheat                      (                    npolygons))
  3020)       allocate(cgrid%baseflow                   (                    npolygons))
  3021)       allocate(cgrid%runoff                     (                    npolygons))
  3022)       allocate(cgrid%qrunoff                    (                    npolygons))

  3767)       !----- Make sure that we nullify all pointers for a safe allocation. ----------------!
  3768)       call nullify_polygontype(cpoly)
  3769)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!

  3784)                          ,'allocate_polygontype','ed_state_vars.f90')

  3943)    !     This subroutine allocates the patch-level variables.                              !
  3944)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3945)    subroutine allocate_sitetype(csite,npatches)
  3946) 
  3947)       implicit none
  3948) 
  3949)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3950)       type(sitetype), target     :: csite
  3951)       integer       , intent(in) :: npatches
  3952)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  3953)       integer                    :: ipa
  3954)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3955) 
  3956) 
  3957)       !----- Make sure that we nullify all pointers for a safe allocation. ----------------!
  3958)       call nullify_sitetype(csite)
  3959)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3960) 
  3961) 
  3962)       !----- Define the number of sites. --------------------------------------------------!
  3963)       csite%npatches = npatches
  3964)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3965) 
  3966) 
  3967)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3968)       !       Up to now, there is no reason for an empty site, so the code will always     !
  3969)       ! assume that there is at least one patch in the site.  In case npatches is zero,    !
  3970)       ! we should stop the run and warn the user.                                          !
  3971)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3972)       if (npatches == 0) then
  3973)          call fatal_error('Attempt to set a site with 0 patches. This cannot happen!'      &
  3974)                          ,'allocate_sitetype','ed_state_vars.f90')
  3975)       end if
  3976)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3977) 
  3978) 
  3979) 
  3980) 
  3981)       allocate(csite%patch  (npatches))
  3982) 
  3983)       !----- Assume that all patches are empty. -------------------------------------------!
  3984)       do ipa=1,npatches
  3985)          csite%patch(ipa)%ncohorts = 0
  3986)       end do
  3987)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  3988)

  3990)       allocate(csite%paco_n                        (              npatches))

  4432)    !=======================================================================================!
  4433) 
  4434) 
  4435) 
  4436)

  4438) 
  4439)    !=======================================================================================! 
  4440)    !=======================================================================================! 
  4441)    !     This subroutine allocates the cohort-level variables.                             !
  4442)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4443)    subroutine allocate_patchtype(cpatch,ncohorts)
  4444) 
  4445)       implicit none
  4446) 
  4447)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4448)       type(patchtype), target     :: cpatch
  4449)       integer        , intent(in) :: ncohorts
  4450)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4451)  
  4452) 
  4453)       !----- Make sure that we nullify all pointers for a safe allocation. ----------------!
  4454)       call nullify_patchtype   (cpatch)
  4455)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4456) 
  4457) 
  4458)       !----- Define the number of cohorts. ------------------------------------------------!
  4459)       cpatch%ncohorts = ncohorts
  4460)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4461) 
  4462) 
  4463)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  4464)       !       Some cohorts may be empty.  If all plants die, or if this simulation is a    !
  4465)       ! true bare ground run, no cohort should exist, in which case we return.             !
  4466)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!

  6700)    !=======================================================================================!
  6701)    !=======================================================================================!
  6702) 
  6703) 
  6704) 
  6705)    !=======================================================================================!
  6706)    !=======================================================================================!
  6707)    !     This sub-routine de-allocates all patch pointers.                                 !
  6708)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6709)    subroutine deallocate_sitetype(csite)
  6710)       implicit none
  6711) 
  6712)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6713)       type(sitetype)   , target :: csite
  6714)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  6715)       integer                   :: ipa
  6716)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6717) 
  6718) 
  6719)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6720)       !     First thing we must do is to deallocate the nested dimensions.                 !
  6721)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6722)       do ipa=1,csite%npatches
  6723)           call deallocate_patchtype(csite%patch(ipa))
  6724)       end do
  6725)       if (associated(csite%patch)) deallocate(csite%patch)
  6726)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  6727) 
  6728)       if(associated(csite%paco_id               )) deallocate(csite%paco_id               )
  6729)       if(associated(csite%paco_n                )) deallocate(csite%paco_n                )
  6730)       if(associated(csite%patch                 )) deallocate(csite%patch                 )
  6731)       if(associated(csite%cohort_count          )) deallocate(csite%cohort_count          )
  6732)       if(associated(csite%pname                 )) deallocate(csite%pname                 )
  6733)       if(associated(csite%area                  )) deallocate(csite%area                  )
  6734)       if(associated(csite%age                   )) deallocate(csite%age                   )
  6735)       if(associated(csite%dist_type             )) deallocate(csite%dist_type             )
  6736)       if(associated(csite%fast_soil_C           )) deallocate(csite%fast_soil_C           )
  6737)       if(associated(csite%slow_soil_C           )) deallocate(csite%slow_soil_C           )
  6738)       if(associated(csite%structural_soil_C     )) deallocate(csite%structural_soil_C     )
  6739)       if(associated(csite%structural_soil_L     )) deallocate(csite%structural_soil_L     )
  6740)       if(associated(csite%mineralized_soil_N    )) deallocate(csite%mineralized_soil_N    )
  6741)       if(associated(csite%fast_soil_N           )) deallocate(csite%fast_soil_N           )
  6742)       if(associated(csite%sum_dgd               )) deallocate(csite%sum_dgd               )
  6743)       if(associated(csite%sum_chd               )) deallocate(csite%sum_chd               )
  6744)       if(associated(csite%can_theiv             )) deallocate(csite%can_theiv             )
  6745)       if(associated(csite%can_vpdef             )) deallocate(csite%can_vpdef             )
  6746)       if(associated(csite%can_temp              )) deallocate(csite%can_temp              )
  6747)       if(associated(csite%can_temp_pv           )) deallocate(csite%can_temp_pv           )
  6748)       if(associated(csite%can_shv               )) deallocate(csite%can_shv               )
  6749)       if(associated(csite%can_co2               )) deallocate(csite%can_co2               )

  7569)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_leaf_hcap     )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_leaf_hcap     )
  7570)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_leaf_vpdef    )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_leaf_vpdef    )
  7571)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_leaf_temp     )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_leaf_temp     )
  7572)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_leaf_fliq     )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_leaf_fliq     )

  7576)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wood_water    )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wood_water    )

  7578)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wood_temp     )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wood_temp     )
  7579)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wood_fliq     )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wood_fliq     )
  7580)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wood_gbw      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wood_gbw      )
  7581)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_fs_open       )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_fs_open       )
  7582)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_fsw           )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_fsw           )
  7583)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_fsn           )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_fsn           )
  7584)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_a_open        )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_a_open        )
  7585)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_a_closed      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_a_closed      )

  7587)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_A_light       )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_A_light       )
  7588)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_A_rubp        )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_A_rubp        )
  7589)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_A_co2         )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_A_co2         )
  7590)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_psi_open      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_psi_open      )
  7591)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_psi_closed    )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_psi_closed    )
  7592)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_water_supply  )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_water_supply  )
  7593)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_light_level   )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_light_level   )
  7594)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_light_level_beam))                                        &
  7595)                                                 deallocate(cpatch%qmean_light_level_beam)

  7598)

  7600)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_par_level_diffu))deallocate(cpatch%qmean_par_level_diffu)
  7601)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_par_level_diffd))deallocate(cpatch%qmean_par_level_diffd)
  7602) 
  7603)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_par_l         )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_par_l         )
  7604)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_par_l_beam    )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_par_l_beam    )
  7605)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_par_l_diff    )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_par_l_diff    )
  7606)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_rshort_l      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_rshort_l      )
  7607)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_rlong_l       )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_rlong_l       )
  7608)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_sensible_lc   )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_sensible_lc   )
  7609)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_vapor_lc      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_vapor_lc      )
  7610)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_transp        )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_transp        )
  7611)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_intercepted_al)) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_intercepted_al)
  7612)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wshed_lg      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wshed_lg      )
  7613)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_rshort_w      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_rshort_w      )
  7614)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_rlong_w       )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_rlong_w       )
  7615)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_rad_profile   )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_rad_profile   )
  7616)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_sensible_wc   )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_sensible_wc   )
  7617)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_vapor_wc      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_vapor_wc      )
  7618)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_intercepted_aw)) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_intercepted_aw)
  7619)       if(associated(cpatch%qmean_wshed_wg      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmean_wshed_wg      )
  7620)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_gpp           )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_gpp           )
  7621)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_npp           )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_npp           )
  7622)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_plresp        )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_plresp        )

  7625)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_transp        )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_transp        )
  7626)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc   )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc   )
  7627)       if(associated(cpatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc      )) deallocate(cpatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc      )

  7630)    end subroutine deallocate_patchtype
  7631)    !=======================================================================================!
  7632)    !=======================================================================================!
  7633) 
  7634) 
  7635) 
  7636) 
  7637) 
  7638) 
  7639)    !=======================================================================================!
  7640)    !=======================================================================================!
  7641)    !     This subroutine copies a continuous chunk of patches from one place to another.   !
  7642)    ! The number of patches to be copied must match between the input and output, and every !
  7643)    ! single variable, including the cohorts, will be copied.                               !
  7644)    ! IMPORTANT.  This subroutine assumes that the output patches still don't have cohorts  !
  7645)    !             allocated, so this should be never used in a previously allocated patch.  !
  7646)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7647)    subroutine copy_sitetype(isite,osite,ipaa,ipaz,opaa,opaz)
  7648)       implicit none
  7649)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7650)       type(sitetype)  , target     :: isite ! Input  (donor) site
  7651)       type(sitetype)  , target     :: osite ! Output (receptor) site
  7652)       integer         , intent(in) :: ipaa  ! First input  patch index
  7653)       integer         , intent(in) :: ipaz  ! Last  input  patch index
  7654)       integer         , intent(in) :: opaa  ! First output patch index
  7655)       integer         , intent(in) :: opaz  ! Last  output patch index
  7656)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  7657)       integer                      :: ipa   ! Counter for the input  site patches
  7658)       integer                      :: opa   ! Counter for the output site patches
  7659)       integer                      :: m     ! First counter
  7660)       integer                      :: n     ! Second counter
  7661)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7662) 
  7663) 
  7664)       !------ Check whether this patch copying makes sense. -------------------------------!
  7665)       if (ipaz - ipaa /= opaz - opaa) then
  7666)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       '------------------------------------------------'
  7667)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       ' - Input site:'
  7668)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * First patch: ',ipaa
  7669)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Last  patch: ',ipaz
  7670)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Patch count: ',ipaz-ipaa+1
  7671)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       ' - Output site:'
  7672)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * First patch: ',opaa
  7673)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Last  patch: ',opaz
  7674)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Patch count: ',opaz-opaa+1
  7675)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)'      ) '------------------------------------------------'
  7676)          call fatal_error ('Patch count of input and output sites don''t match'            &
  7677)                           ,'copy_sitetype','ed_state_vars.f90')
  7678)       end if
  7679)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7680) 
  7681) 
  7682) 
  7683)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7684)       !     First we copy the cohorts.                                                     !
  7685)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7686)       ipa = ipaa - 1
  7687)       opaloop: do opa = opaa, opaz
  7688)          ipa = ipa + 1
  7689)          !----- Copy all cohorts. ---------------------------------------------------------!
  7690)          call allocate_patchtype(osite%patch(opa),isite%patch(ipa)%ncohorts)
  7691)          call copy_patchtype    (isite%patch(ipa),osite%patch(opa)                         &
  7692)                                 ,1,isite%patch(ipa)%ncohorts,1,isite%patch(ipa)%ncohorts)
  7693)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7694) 
  7695) 
  7696)          !----- Scalars. ------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7697)          osite%paco_id                    (opa) = isite%paco_id                    (ipa)
  7698)          osite%paco_n                     (opa) = isite%paco_n                     (ipa)
  7699)          osite%cohort_count               (opa) = isite%cohort_count               (ipa)
  7700)          osite%pname                      (opa) = isite%pname                      (ipa)
  7701)          osite%area                       (opa) = isite%area                       (ipa)
  7702)          osite%age                        (opa) = isite%age                        (ipa)
  7703)          osite%dist_type                  (opa) = isite%dist_type                  (ipa)
  7704)          osite%fast_soil_C                (opa) = isite%fast_soil_C                (ipa)
  7705)          osite%slow_soil_C                (opa) = isite%slow_soil_C                (ipa)
  7706)          osite%structural_soil_C          (opa) = isite%structural_soil_C          (ipa)
  7707)          osite%structural_soil_L          (opa) = isite%structural_soil_L          (ipa)
  7708)          osite%mineralized_soil_N         (opa) = isite%mineralized_soil_N         (ipa)
  7709)          osite%fast_soil_N                (opa) = isite%fast_soil_N                (ipa)
  7710)          osite%sum_dgd                    (opa) = isite%sum_dgd                    (ipa)
  7711)          osite%sum_chd                    (opa) = isite%sum_chd                    (ipa)
  7712)          osite%can_theiv                  (opa) = isite%can_theiv                  (ipa)
  7713)          osite%can_vpdef                  (opa) = isite%can_vpdef                  (ipa)
  7714)          osite%can_temp                   (opa) = isite%can_temp                   (ipa)
  7715)          osite%can_temp_pv                (opa) = isite%can_temp_pv                (ipa)
  7716)          osite%can_shv                    (opa) = isite%can_shv                    (ipa)
  7717)          osite%can_co2                    (opa) = isite%can_co2                    (ipa)
  7718)          osite%can_rhos                   (opa) = isite%can_rhos                   (ipa)
  7719)          osite%can_prss                   (opa) = isite%can_prss                   (ipa)
  7720)          osite%can_theta                  (opa) = isite%can_theta                  (ipa)
  7721)          osite%can_depth                  (opa) = isite%can_depth                  (ipa)
  7722)          osite%opencan_frac               (opa) = isite%opencan_frac               (ipa)
  7723)          osite%ggbare                     (opa) = isite%ggbare                     (ipa)
  7724)          osite%ggveg                      (opa) = isite%ggveg                      (ipa)

  7990)             osite%dmean_qrunoff        (opa) = isite%dmean_qrunoff        (ipa)
  7991)             osite%dmean_qdrainage      (opa) = isite%dmean_qdrainage      (ipa)
  7992)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  7993) 
  7994) 
  7995)             !----- Soil variables. --------------------------------------------------------!
  7996)             do m=1,nzg
  7997)                osite%dmean_soil_energy(m,opa) = isite%dmean_soil_energy(m,ipa)
  7998)                osite%dmean_soil_mstpot(m,opa) = isite%dmean_soil_mstpot(m,ipa)
  7999)                osite%dmean_soil_water (m,opa) = isite%dmean_soil_water (m,ipa)
  8000)                osite%dmean_soil_temp  (m,opa) = isite%dmean_soil_temp  (m,ipa)
  8001)                osite%dmean_soil_fliq  (m,opa) = isite%dmean_soil_fliq  (m,ipa)

  8004)                osite%dmean_sensible_gg(m,opa) = isite%dmean_sensible_gg(m,ipa)

  8007)          end if

  8130)                osite%qmean_can_theta      (n,opa) = isite%qmean_can_theta      (n,ipa)
  8131)                osite%qmean_can_vpdef      (n,opa) = isite%qmean_can_vpdef      (n,ipa)
  8132)                osite%qmean_can_temp       (n,opa) = isite%qmean_can_temp       (n,ipa)

  8144)                osite%qmean_sfcw_fliq      (n,opa) = isite%qmean_sfcw_fliq      (n,ipa)
  8145)                osite%qmean_rshort_gnd     (n,opa) = isite%qmean_rshort_gnd     (n,ipa)

  8148)                osite%qmean_rlongup        (n,opa) = isite%qmean_rlongup        (n,ipa)
  8149)                osite%qmean_parup          (n,opa) = isite%qmean_parup          (n,ipa)
  8150)                osite%qmean_nirup          (n,opa) = isite%qmean_nirup          (n,ipa)

  8153)                osite%qmean_albedo         (n,opa) = isite%qmean_albedo         (n,ipa)
  8154)                osite%qmean_albedo_par     (n,opa) = isite%qmean_albedo_par     (n,ipa)

  8169)                osite%qmean_sensible_ac    (n,opa) = isite%qmean_sensible_ac    (n,ipa)
  8170)                osite%qmean_qthroughfall   (n,opa) = isite%qmean_qthroughfall   (n,ipa)
  8171)                osite%qmean_qrunoff        (n,opa) = isite%qmean_qrunoff        (n,ipa)
  8172)                osite%qmean_qdrainage      (n,opa) = isite%qmean_qdrainage      (n,ipa)

  8176)                osite%qmsqu_rlongup        (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_rlongup        (n,ipa)
  8177)                osite%qmsqu_parup          (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_parup          (n,ipa)
  8178)                osite%qmsqu_nirup          (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_nirup          (n,ipa)
  8179)                osite%qmsqu_rshortup       (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_rshortup       (n,ipa)
  8180)                osite%qmsqu_rnet           (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_rnet           (n,ipa)
  8181)                osite%qmsqu_albedo         (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_albedo         (n,ipa)
  8182)                osite%qmsqu_ustar          (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_ustar          (n,ipa)
  8183)                osite%qmsqu_carbon_ac      (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_carbon_ac      (n,ipa)
  8184)                osite%qmsqu_carbon_st      (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_carbon_st      (n,ipa)

  8188)                osite%qmsqu_sensible_ac    (n,opa) = isite%qmsqu_sensible_ac    (n,ipa)

  8191) 
  8192)                !----- Soil variables. -----------------------------------------------------!

  8194)                   osite%qmean_soil_energy(m,n,opa) = isite%qmean_soil_energy(m,n,ipa)

  8209)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8210)

  8212)    end subroutine copy_sitetype
  8213)    !=======================================================================================!
  8214)    !=======================================================================================!
  8215) 
  8216) 
  8217) 
  8218) 
  8219) 
  8220)    !=======================================================================================!
  8221)    !=======================================================================================!
  8222)    !      This subroutine copies part of one patch to another (only the ones where mask    !
  8223)    ! is .true.).  Please notice the following requirements.                                !
  8224)    !                                                                                       !
  8225)    !      1. ISITE and LMASK must have dimension MASKSZ                                    !
  8226)    !      2. OSITE must have dimension NEWSZ                                               !
  8227)    !      3. The number of .true. elements of LMASK must be NEWSZ                          !
  8228)    !      This subroutine assumes that the size of vectors in osite is the number of true  !
  8229)    ! elements in mask, whilst the size of the vectors in isite must be the size of the     !
  8230)    ! mask itself.                                                                          !
  8231)    !                                                                                       !
  8232)    ! IMPORTANT:  This routine currently assumes that the output site has not allocated     !
  8233)    !             any cohort yet, because the length of these nested vectors depend on the  !
  8234)    !             donor patch vector sizes.  Never call this sub-routine if osite has been  !
  8235)    !             allocated before.                                                         !
  8236)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8237)    subroutine copy_sitetype_mask(isite,osite,lmask,isize,osize)
  8238) 
  8239) 
  8240)       implicit none
  8241)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8242)       type(sitetype)                  , target     :: isite   ! Input  (donor) site
  8243)       type(sitetype)                  , target     :: osite   ! Output (receptor) site
  8244)       integer                         , intent(in) :: isize   ! Input size 
  8245)       integer                         , intent(in) :: osize   ! Output size
  8246)       logical       , dimension(isize), intent(in) :: lmask   ! Mask
  8247)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  8248)       integer       , dimension(isize)             :: allind
  8249)       integer       , dimension(osize)             :: iindex
  8250)       integer                                      :: o
  8251)       integer                                      :: i
  8252)       integer                                      :: z
  8253)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8254) 
  8255) 
  8256)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8257)       !     Map the indices between the input and the output vectors.                      !
  8258)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8259)       z = count(lmask)
  8260)       !----- Crash if the dimensions don't match. -----------------------------------------!
  8261)       if (z /= osize) then
  8262)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i12)') ' Z     = ',z
  8263)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i12)') ' OSIZE = ',osize
  8264)          call fatal_error('Mask doesn''t have OSIZE .true. elements'                       &
  8265)                          ,'copy_sitetype_mask','ed_state_vars.f90')
  8266)       end if
  8267) 
  8268)       !----- Save the indices from where we are going to copy. ----------------------------!
  8269)       allind = (/ (i,i=1,isize) /)
  8270)       iindex = pack(allind,lmask)
  8271)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8272) 
  8273)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8274)       !      Copy the cohorts.                                                             !
  8275)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8276)       do o=1,osize
  8277)          i = iindex(o)
  8278)          call allocate_patchtype(osite%patch(o),isite%patch(i)%ncohorts)
  8279)          call copy_patchtype    (isite%patch(i),osite%patch(o)                             &
  8280)                                 ,1,isite%patch(i)%ncohorts,1,osite%patch(o)%ncohorts)
  8281)       end do
  8282)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8283) 
  8284) 
  8285)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8286)       !      We break the subroutines into smaller pieces so Fortran doesn't complain...   !
  8287)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8288)       call copy_sitetype_mask_inst (isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
  8289)       call copy_sitetype_mask_fmean(isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
  8290)       if (writing_long) call copy_sitetype_mask_dmean(isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
  8291)       if (writing_eorq) call copy_sitetype_mask_mmean(isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
  8292)       if (writing_dcyc) call copy_sitetype_mask_qmean(isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
  8293)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8294) 
  8295)       return
  8296)    end subroutine copy_sitetype_mask

  8299) 
  8300) 
  8301) 
  8302)

  8521)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8522)    subroutine copy_sitetype_mask_fmean(isite,osite,z,lmask,isize)
