  8961)    !=======================================================================================!
  8962)    !=======================================================================================!
  8963)    !     This subroutine copies a continuous chunk of patches from one place to another.   !
  8964)    ! The number of patches to be copied must match between the input and output, and every !
  8965)    ! single variable, including the cohorts, will be copied.                               !
  8966)    ! IMPORTANT.  This subroutine assumes that the output patches still don't have cohorts  !
  8967)    !             allocated, so this should be never used in a previously allocated patch.  !
  8968)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8969)    subroutine copy_patchtype(ipatch,opatch,icoa,icoz,ocoa,ocoz)
  8970)       implicit none
  8971)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8972)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: ipatch
  8973)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: opatch
  8974)       integer                 , intent(in) :: icoa
  8975)       integer                 , intent(in) :: icoz
  8976)       integer                 , intent(in) :: ocoa
  8977)       integer                 , intent(in) :: ocoz
  8978)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  8979)       integer                              :: ico
  8980)       integer                              :: oco
  8981)       integer                              :: m
  8982)       integer                              :: n
  8983)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  8984) 
  8985) 
  8986)       !------ Check whether this cohort copying makes sense. ------------------------------!
  8987)       if (icoz - icoa /= ocoz - ocoa) then
  8988)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       '------------------------------------------------'
  8989)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       ' - Input patch:'
  8990)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * First cohort: ',icoa
  8991)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Last  cohort: ',icoz
  8992)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Cohort count: ',icoz-icoa+1
  8993)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       ' - Output site:'
  8994)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * First cohort: ',ocoa
  8995)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Last  cohort: ',ocoz
  8996)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i6)') '   * Cohort count: ',ocoz-ocoa+1
  8997)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)'      ) '------------------------------------------------'
  8998)          call fatal_error ('Cohort count of input and output patches don''t match'         &
  8999)                           ,'copy_patchtype','ed_state_vars.f90')
  9000)       end if
  9001)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9002) 
  9003)       ico = icoa - 1
  9004)       cohortloop: do oco = ocoa,ocoz
  9005)          ico = ico + 1
  9006) 
  9007)          !----- Scalars. ------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9008)          opatch%pft                   (oco) = ipatch%pft                   (ico)
  9009)          opatch%nplant                (oco) = ipatch%nplant                (ico)
  9010)          opatch%phenology_status      (oco) = ipatch%phenology_status      (ico)
  9011)          opatch%recruit_dbh           (oco) = ipatch%recruit_dbh           (ico)
  9012)          opatch%census_status         (oco) = ipatch%census_status         (ico)
  9013)          opatch%hite                  (oco) = ipatch%hite                  (ico)
  9014)          opatch%agb                   (oco) = ipatch%agb                   (ico)
  9015)          opatch%basarea               (oco) = ipatch%basarea               (ico)
  9016)          opatch%dagb_dt               (oco) = ipatch%dagb_dt               (ico)
  9017)          opatch%dlnagb_dt             (oco) = ipatch%dlnagb_dt             (ico)
  9018)          opatch%dba_dt                (oco) = ipatch%dba_dt                (ico)
  9019)          opatch%dlnba_dt              (oco) = ipatch%dlnba_dt              (ico)
  9020)          opatch%ddbh_dt               (oco) = ipatch%ddbh_dt               (ico)
  9021)          opatch%dlndbh_dt             (oco) = ipatch%dlndbh_dt             (ico)
  9022)          opatch%dbh                   (oco) = ipatch%dbh                   (ico)
  9023)          opatch%bdead                 (oco) = ipatch%bdead                 (ico)
  9024)          opatch%bleaf                 (oco) = ipatch%bleaf                 (ico)
  9025)          opatch%balive                (oco) = ipatch%balive                (ico)
  9026)          opatch%broot                 (oco) = ipatch%broot                 (ico)
  9027)          opatch%bsapwooda             (oco) = ipatch%bsapwooda             (ico)
  9028)          opatch%bsapwoodb             (oco) = ipatch%bsapwoodb             (ico)
  9029)          opatch%bstorage              (oco) = ipatch%bstorage              (ico)
  9030)          opatch%bseeds                (oco) = ipatch%bseeds                (ico)
  9031)          opatch%lai                   (oco) = ipatch%lai                   (ico)
  9032)          opatch%wai                   (oco) = ipatch%wai                   (ico)
  9033)          opatch%crown_area            (oco) = ipatch%crown_area            (ico)
  9034)          opatch%leaf_resolvable       (oco) = ipatch%leaf_resolvable       (ico)
  9035)          opatch%wood_resolvable       (oco) = ipatch%wood_resolvable       (ico)
  9036)          opatch%cbr_bar               (oco) = ipatch%cbr_bar               (ico)
  9037)          opatch%leaf_energy           (oco) = ipatch%leaf_energy           (ico)
  9038)          opatch%leaf_temp             (oco) = ipatch%leaf_temp             (ico)
  9039)          opatch%leaf_vpdef            (oco) = ipatch%leaf_vpdef            (ico)
  9040)          opatch%leaf_temp_pv          (oco) = ipatch%leaf_temp_pv          (ico)
  9041)          opatch%leaf_hcap             (oco) = ipatch%leaf_hcap             (ico)
  9042)          opatch%leaf_fliq             (oco) = ipatch%leaf_fliq             (ico)
  9043)          opatch%leaf_water            (oco) = ipatch%leaf_water            (ico)
  9044)          opatch%wood_energy           (oco) = ipatch%wood_energy           (ico)
  9045)          opatch%wood_temp             (oco) = ipatch%wood_temp             (ico)
  9046)          opatch%wood_temp_pv          (oco) = ipatch%wood_temp_pv          (ico)

  9052)          opatch%lsfc_shv_closed       (oco) = ipatch%lsfc_shv_closed       (ico)
  9053)          opatch%lsfc_co2_open         (oco) = ipatch%lsfc_co2_open         (ico)
  9054)          opatch%lsfc_co2_closed       (oco) = ipatch%lsfc_co2_closed       (ico)
  9055)          opatch%lint_shv              (oco) = ipatch%lint_shv              (ico)

  9058)          opatch%today_leaf_resp       (oco) = ipatch%today_leaf_resp       (ico)
  9059)          opatch%today_root_resp       (oco) = ipatch%today_root_resp       (ico)
  9060)          opatch%today_gpp             (oco) = ipatch%today_gpp             (ico)

  9069)          opatch%today_nppseeds        (oco) = ipatch%today_nppseeds        (ico)
  9070)          opatch%today_nppwood         (oco) = ipatch%today_nppwood         (ico)
  9071)          opatch%today_nppdaily        (oco) = ipatch%today_nppdaily        (ico)
  9072)          opatch%leaf_growth_resp      (oco) = ipatch%leaf_growth_resp      (ico)
  9073)          opatch%root_growth_resp      (oco) = ipatch%root_growth_resp      (ico)
  9074)          opatch%sapa_growth_resp      (oco) = ipatch%sapa_growth_resp      (ico)

  9078)          opatch%sapa_storage_resp     (oco) = ipatch%sapa_storage_resp     (ico)
  9079)          opatch%sapb_storage_resp     (oco) = ipatch%sapb_storage_resp     (ico)
  9080)          opatch%monthly_dndt          (oco) = ipatch%monthly_dndt          (ico)
  9081)          opatch%monthly_dlnndt        (oco) = ipatch%monthly_dlnndt        (ico)

  9381)             opatch%mmean_sensible_lc     (oco) = ipatch%mmean_sensible_lc     (ico)
  9382)             opatch%mmean_vapor_lc        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_vapor_lc        (ico)
  9383)             opatch%mmean_transp          (oco) = ipatch%mmean_transp          (ico)
  9384)             opatch%mmean_intercepted_al  (oco) = ipatch%mmean_intercepted_al  (ico)
  9385)             opatch%mmean_wshed_lg        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_wshed_lg        (ico)
  9386)             opatch%mmean_rshort_w        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_rshort_w        (ico)
  9387)             opatch%mmean_rlong_w         (oco) = ipatch%mmean_rlong_w         (ico)
  9388)             opatch%mmean_sensible_wc     (oco) = ipatch%mmean_sensible_wc     (ico)
  9389)             opatch%mmean_vapor_wc        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_vapor_wc        (ico)
  9390)             opatch%mmean_intercepted_aw  (oco) = ipatch%mmean_intercepted_aw  (ico)
  9391)             opatch%mmean_wshed_wg        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_wshed_wg        (ico)
  9392)             opatch%mmean_nppleaf         (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppleaf         (ico)
  9393)             opatch%mmean_nppfroot        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppfroot        (ico)
  9394)             opatch%mmean_nppsapwood      (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppsapwood      (ico)
  9395)             opatch%mmean_nppcroot        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppcroot        (ico)
  9396)             opatch%mmean_nppseeds        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppseeds        (ico)
  9397)             opatch%mmean_nppwood         (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppwood         (ico)
  9398)             opatch%mmean_nppdaily        (oco) = ipatch%mmean_nppdaily        (ico)
  9399)             opatch%mmsqu_gpp             (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_gpp             (ico)
  9400)             opatch%mmsqu_npp             (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_npp             (ico)
  9401)             opatch%mmsqu_plresp          (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_plresp          (ico)
  9402)             opatch%mmsqu_sensible_lc     (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_sensible_lc     (ico)
  9403)             opatch%mmsqu_vapor_lc        (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_vapor_lc        (ico)
  9404)             opatch%mmsqu_transp          (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_transp          (ico)
  9405)             opatch%mmsqu_sensible_wc     (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_sensible_wc     (ico)
  9406)             opatch%mmsqu_vapor_wc        (oco) = ipatch%mmsqu_vapor_wc        (ico)
  9407)             !----- Mortality variables. ---------------------------------------------------!
  9408)             do m=1,n_mort
  9409)                opatch%mmean_mort_rate(m,oco) = ipatch%mmean_mort_rate(m,ico)
  9410)             end do
  9411)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9412) 
  9413)             !------ Radiation profile variables. ------------------------------------------!
  9414)             do m=1,n_radprof
  9415)                opatch%mmean_rad_profile(m,oco) = ipatch%mmean_rad_profile(m,ico)
  9416)             end do
  9417)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9418)          end if
  9419)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9420) 
  9421) 
  9422) 
  9423)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9424)          !     Mean diel.                                                                  !
  9425)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9426) 
  9427)          if (writing_dcyc) then
  9428)             do n=1,ndcycle
  9429)                opatch%qmean_gpp             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_gpp             (n,ico)
  9430)                opatch%qmean_npp             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_npp             (n,ico)
  9431)                opatch%qmean_leaf_resp       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_resp       (n,ico)
  9432)                opatch%qmean_root_resp       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_root_resp       (n,ico)
  9433)                opatch%qmean_leaf_growth_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_growth_resp(n,ico)
  9434)                opatch%qmean_root_growth_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_root_growth_resp(n,ico)
  9435)                opatch%qmean_sapa_growth_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sapa_growth_resp(n,ico)
  9436)                opatch%qmean_sapb_growth_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sapb_growth_resp(n,ico)
  9437)                opatch%qmean_leaf_storage_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_storage_resp(n,ico)
  9438)                opatch%qmean_root_storage_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_root_storage_resp(n,ico)
  9439)                opatch%qmean_sapa_storage_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sapa_storage_resp(n,ico)
  9440)                opatch%qmean_sapb_storage_resp(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sapb_storage_resp(n,ico)
  9441)                opatch%qmean_plresp          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_plresp          (n,ico)
  9442)                opatch%qmean_leaf_energy     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_energy     (n,ico)
  9443)                opatch%qmean_leaf_water      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_water      (n,ico)
  9444)                opatch%qmean_leaf_hcap       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_hcap       (n,ico)
  9445)                opatch%qmean_leaf_vpdef      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_vpdef      (n,ico)
  9446)                opatch%qmean_leaf_temp       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_temp       (n,ico)
  9447)                opatch%qmean_leaf_fliq       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_fliq       (n,ico)
  9448)                opatch%qmean_leaf_gsw        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_gsw        (n,ico)
  9449)                opatch%qmean_leaf_gbw        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_leaf_gbw        (n,ico)
  9450)                opatch%qmean_wood_energy     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_energy     (n,ico)
  9451)                opatch%qmean_wood_water      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_water      (n,ico)
  9452)                opatch%qmean_wood_hcap       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_hcap       (n,ico)
  9453)                opatch%qmean_wood_temp       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_temp       (n,ico)
  9454)                opatch%qmean_wood_fliq       (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_fliq       (n,ico)
  9455)                opatch%qmean_wood_gbw        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wood_gbw        (n,ico)
  9456)                opatch%qmean_fs_open         (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_fs_open         (n,ico)
  9457)                opatch%qmean_fsw             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_fsw             (n,ico)
  9458)                opatch%qmean_fsn             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_fsn             (n,ico)
  9459)                opatch%qmean_a_open          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_a_open          (n,ico)
  9460)                opatch%qmean_a_closed        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_a_closed        (n,ico)
  9461)                opatch%qmean_a_net           (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_a_net           (n,ico)
  9462)                opatch%qmean_A_light         (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_A_light         (n,ico)
  9463)                opatch%qmean_A_rubp          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_A_rubp          (n,ico)
  9464)                opatch%qmean_A_co2           (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_A_co2           (n,ico)
  9465)                opatch%qmean_psi_open        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_psi_open        (n,ico)
  9466)                opatch%qmean_psi_closed      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_psi_closed      (n,ico)
  9467)                opatch%qmean_water_supply    (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_water_supply    (n,ico)
  9468)                opatch%qmean_light_level     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_light_level     (n,ico)
  9469)                opatch%qmean_light_level_beam(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_light_level_beam(n,ico)
  9470)                opatch%qmean_light_level_diff(n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_light_level_diff(n,ico)
  9471) 
  9472)                opatch%qmean_par_level_beam  (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_level_beam  (n,ico)
  9473)                opatch%qmean_par_level_diffu (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_level_diffu (n,ico)
  9474)                opatch%qmean_par_level_diffd (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_level_diffd (n,ico)
  9475) 
  9476)                opatch%qmean_par_l           (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_l           (n,ico)
  9477)                opatch%qmean_par_l_beam      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_l_beam      (n,ico)
  9478)                opatch%qmean_par_l_diff      (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_par_l_diff      (n,ico)
  9479)                opatch%qmean_rshort_l        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_rshort_l        (n,ico)
  9480)                opatch%qmean_rlong_l         (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_rlong_l         (n,ico)
  9481)                opatch%qmean_sensible_lc     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sensible_lc     (n,ico)
  9482)                opatch%qmean_vapor_lc        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_vapor_lc        (n,ico)
  9483)                opatch%qmean_transp          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_transp          (n,ico)
  9484)                opatch%qmean_intercepted_al  (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_intercepted_al  (n,ico)

  9486)                opatch%qmean_rshort_w        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_rshort_w        (n,ico)
  9487)                opatch%qmean_rlong_w         (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_rlong_w         (n,ico)
  9488)                opatch%qmean_sensible_wc     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_sensible_wc     (n,ico)
  9489)                opatch%qmean_vapor_wc        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_vapor_wc        (n,ico)
  9490)                opatch%qmean_intercepted_aw  (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_intercepted_aw  (n,ico)
  9491)                opatch%qmean_wshed_wg        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_wshed_wg        (n,ico)
  9492)                opatch%qmsqu_gpp             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_gpp             (n,ico)
  9493)                opatch%qmsqu_npp             (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_npp             (n,ico)
  9494)                opatch%qmsqu_plresp          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_plresp          (n,ico)
  9495)                opatch%qmsqu_sensible_lc     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_sensible_lc     (n,ico)
  9496)                opatch%qmsqu_vapor_lc        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_vapor_lc        (n,ico)
  9497)                opatch%qmsqu_transp          (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_transp          (n,ico)
  9498)                opatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc     (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc     (n,ico)
  9499)                opatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc        (n,oco) = ipatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc        (n,ico)
  9500) 
  9501)                !------ Radiation profile variables. ---------------------------------------!
  9502)                do m=1,n_radprof
  9503)                   opatch%qmean_rad_profile(m,n,oco) = ipatch%qmean_rad_profile(m,n,ico)
  9504)                end do
  9505)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9506)             end do
  9507)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9508)          end if
  9509)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9510)       end do cohortloop
  9511) 
  9512)       return
  9513)    end subroutine copy_patchtype
  9514)    !=======================================================================================!
  9515)    !=======================================================================================!
  9516) 
  9517) 
  9518) 
  9519) 
  9520) 
  9521)    !=======================================================================================!
  9522)    !=======================================================================================!
  9523)    !      This subroutine copies part of one cohort to another (only the ones where mask   !
  9524)    ! is .true.).  Please notice the following requirements.                                !
  9525)    !                                                                                       !
  9526)    !      1. IPATCH and LMASK must have dimension MASKSZ                                   !
  9527)    !      2. OPATCH must have dimension NEWSZ                                              !
  9528)    !      3. The number of .true. elements of LMASK must be NEWSZ                          !
  9529)    !                                                                                       !
  9530)    !      In case these conditions aren't met, then the code will crash due to             !
  9531)    ! segmentation violation.                                                               !
  9532)    !                                                                                       !
  9533)    !      Also, NEVER use this sub-routine for a pre-allocated OPATCH.  This will try to   !
  9534)    ! allocate cohorts and you may experience horrible memory leaks.                        !
  9535)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9536)    subroutine copy_patchtype_mask(ipatch,opatch,lmask,isize,osize)
  9537)       implicit none
  9538)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9539)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: ipatch
  9540)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: opatch
  9541)       integer                 , intent(in) :: isize
  9542)       integer                 , intent(in) :: osize
  9543)       logical,dimension(isize), intent(in) :: lmask
  9544)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  9545)       integer                              :: z
  9546)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9547) 
  9548) 
  9549)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9550)       !     Map the indices between the input and the output vectors.                      !
  9551)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9552)       z = count(lmask)
  9553)       !----- Crash if the dimensions don't match. -----------------------------------------!
  9554)       if (z /= osize) then
  9555)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i12)') ' Z     = ',z
  9556)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i12)') ' OSIZE = ',osize
  9557)          call fatal_error('Mask doesn''t have OSIZE .true. elements'                       &
  9558)                          ,'copy_sitetype_mask','ed_state_vars.f90')
  9559)       end if
  9560)       !----- In case nothing should be copied, we return. ---------------------------------!
  9561)       if (z == 0) return
  9562)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9563) 
  9564) 
  9565) 
  9566)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9567)       !      Fortran doesn't like sub-routines that call too many sub-routines or          !
  9568)       ! functions.  We split the packing procedure to reduce the number of calls per       !
  9569)       ! procedure and make the compilation more efficient.                                 !
  9570)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9571)       call copy_patchtype_mask_inst (ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9572)       call copy_patchtype_mask_fmean(ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9573)       if (writing_long) call copy_patchtype_mask_dmean(ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9574)       if (writing_eorq) call copy_patchtype_mask_mmean(ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9575)       if (writing_dcyc) call copy_patchtype_mask_qmean(ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9576)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9577) 
  9578)       return
  9579)    end subroutine copy_patchtype_mask
  9580)    !=======================================================================================!
  9581)    !=======================================================================================!
  9582) 
  9583) 
  9584) 
  9585) 
  9586) 
  9587)    !=======================================================================================!
  9588)    !=======================================================================================!
  9589)    !     This sub-routine copies the cohort-level variables that are not fmean, mmean,     !
  9590)    ! mmsqu, qmean, qmsqu.  The only sub-routine that should ever call this one is          !
  9591)    ! copy_patchtype_mask.                                                                  !
  9592)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9593)    subroutine copy_patchtype_mask_inst(ipatch,opatch,z,lmask,isize)
  9594)       implicit none
  9595)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9596)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: ipatch
  9597)       type(patchtype)         , target     :: opatch

  9599)       integer                 , intent(in) :: isize
  9600)       logical,dimension(isize), intent(in) :: lmask
  9601)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
  9602)       integer                              :: m
  9603)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9604) 
  9605) 
  9606) 
  9607)       !----- Scalars. ---------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9608)       opatch%pft                   (1:z) = pack(ipatch%pft                       ,lmask)
  9609)       opatch%nplant                (1:z) = pack(ipatch%nplant                    ,lmask)

  9622)       opatch%dbh                   (1:z) = pack(ipatch%dbh                       ,lmask)
  9623)       opatch%bdead                 (1:z) = pack(ipatch%bdead                     ,lmask)
  9624)       opatch%bleaf                 (1:z) = pack(ipatch%bleaf                     ,lmask)
  9625)       opatch%balive                (1:z) = pack(ipatch%balive                    ,lmask)

  9639)       opatch%leaf_vpdef            (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_vpdef                ,lmask)
  9640)       opatch%leaf_temp_pv          (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_temp_pv              ,lmask)
  9641)       opatch%leaf_hcap             (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_hcap                 ,lmask)
  9642)       opatch%leaf_fliq             (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_fliq                 ,lmask)
  9643)       opatch%leaf_water            (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_water                ,lmask)

  9658)       opatch%today_leaf_resp       (1:z) = pack(ipatch%today_leaf_resp           ,lmask)
  9659)       opatch%today_root_resp       (1:z) = pack(ipatch%today_root_resp           ,lmask)
  9660)       opatch%today_gpp             (1:z) = pack(ipatch%today_gpp                 ,lmask)
  9661)       opatch%today_gpp_pot         (1:z) = pack(ipatch%today_gpp_pot             ,lmask)

  9671)       opatch%today_nppdaily        (1:z) = pack(ipatch%today_nppdaily            ,lmask)
  9672)       opatch%leaf_growth_resp      (1:z) = pack(ipatch%leaf_growth_resp          ,lmask)
  9673)       opatch%root_growth_resp      (1:z) = pack(ipatch%root_growth_resp          ,lmask)

  9745) 
  9746)

  9750)       end do

  9757)       end do
  9758)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
  9759) 
  9760)       return
  9761)    end subroutine copy_patchtype_mask_inst

 10202)          opatch%qmsqu_vapor_lc      (n,1:z) = pack(ipatch%qmsqu_vapor_lc      (n,:),lmask)
 10203)          opatch%qmsqu_transp        (n,1:z) = pack(ipatch%qmsqu_transp        (n,:),lmask)
 10204)          opatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc   (n,1:z) = pack(ipatch%qmsqu_sensible_wc   (n,:),lmask)
 10205)          opatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc      (n,1:z) = pack(ipatch%qmsqu_vapor_wc      (n,:),lmask)
 10206) 
 10207) 
 10208) 
 10209)          !------ Radiation profile variables. ---------------------------------------------!
 10210)          do m=1,n_radprof
 10211)             opatch%qmean_rad_profile(m,n,1:z) = pack(ipatch%qmean_rad_profile(m,n,:),lmask)
 10212)          end do
 10213)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10214) 
 10215)       end do
 10216)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10217) 
 10218) 
 10219)       return
 10220)    end subroutine copy_patchtype_mask_qmean
 10221)    !=======================================================================================!
 10222)    !=======================================================================================!
 10223) 
 10224) 
 10225) 
 10226) 
 10227) 
 10228) 
 10229)    !=======================================================================================!
 10230)    !=======================================================================================!
 10231)    !      This subroutine is the main driver for filling the variable table (var_table) of !
 10232)    ! ED variables.  On a serial computing environment, this routine should be called near  !
 10233)    ! the end of the initialization process after the hierarchical tree structure has been  !
 10234)    ! trimmed via fusion/splitting/termination.  Similiarly, this routine should be called  !
 10235)    ! after any fusion/splitting/termination process, assuming that the major vtable        !
 10236)    ! structures have been deallocated prior to reallocation.                               !
 10237)    !                                                                                       !
 10238)    !      In a parallel environment, this routine should operate in a similiar fashion on  !
 10239)    ! each of the compute nodes.  It is designed such that the compute nodes will write     !
 10240)    ! hyperslabs of data in parallel to a joining HDF5 dataset as "collective-chunked"      !
 10241)    ! data.  The modifications that must be made after running this subroutine, are that    !
 10242)    ! the indexes should account for the offset of the current compute node.                !
 10243)    !                                                                                       !!
 10244)    !    The various state scalars, vectors and arrays are now populate the vtable.  The    !
 10245)    ! vtable indexes the array gives it a name, records its dimensions, when it is to be    !
 10246)    ! used as output and how (averaging and such) and most importantly saves a pointer to   !
 10247)    ! its starting position.  If this routine is being called as a compute node in          !
 10248)    ! parallel, the first position is not necessarily the first position of the whole       !
 10249)    ! datavector, but will only be the first position of that nodes hyperslab chunk         !
 10250)    ! within the given continuous dataset.                                                  !
 10251)    !                                                                                       !
 10252)    ! The first number correspond to the data level:                                        !
 10253)    !    1. Gridtype     (polygon level)                                                    !
 10254)    !    2. Polygontype  (site    level)                                                    !
 10255)    !    3. Sitetype     (patch   level)                                                    !
 10256)    !    4. Patchtype    (cohort  level)                                                    !
 10257)    !    9. Scalar                                                                          !
 10258)    !                                                                                       !
 10259)    ! The other numbers correspond to the kind of dimension and variable.                   !
 10260)    !    0. Main vector ordinate only, integer.                                             !
 10261)    !    1. Main vector ordinate only, real.                                                !
 10262)    !    2. Soil layer                                                                      !
 10263)    !    3. Surface water layer                                                             !
 10264)    !    4. PFT                                                                             !
 10265)    !    5. Disturbance Type                                                                !
 10266)    !    6. DBH class                                                                       !
 10267)    !    7. FF_DBH class                                                                    !
 10268)    !    8. Mortality                                                                       !
 10269)    !    9. Month/13 months                                                                 !
 10270)    !                                                                                       !
 10271)    ! The negative sign means that the variable has an extra dimension, for the diurnal     !
 10272)    !    cycle output.                                                                      !
 10273)    !                                                                                       !
 10274)    ! Of these possible dimensions (2-9), they may be used concurrently to partition the    !
 10275)    !    data into multi-dimensional spaces, but all seven will not be used simultaneously. !
 10276)    !    Currently the highest ranks in use is 3, and you should think twice before making  !
 10277)    !    new types with higher dimensionality: these arrays may become huge.                !
 10278)    !                                                                                       !
 10279)    ! Each unique combination will have a call number associated with it.                   !
 10280)    !                                                                                       !
 10281)    !  10    : rank 1 : polygon, integer                                                    !
 10282)    !  11    : rank 1 : polygon                                                             !
 10283)    ! -11    : rank 2 : polygon, diurnal cycle                                              !
 10284)    !  12    : rank 2 : polygon, s-layer                                                    !
 10285)    !  120   : rank 2 : polygon, s-layer, integer                                           !
 10286)    ! -12    : rank 3 : polygon, diurnal cycle, s-layer                                     !
 10287)    !  13    : rank 2 : polygon, w-layer                                                    !
 10288)    !  14    : rank 2 : polygon, pft                                                        !
 10289)    !  146   : rank 3 : polygon, pft, dbh                                                   !
 10290)    !  15    : rank 2 : polygon, disturbance                                                !
 10291)    !  155   : rank 3 : polygon, disturbance, disturbance                                   !
 10292)    !  157   : rank 3 : polygon, disturbance, age                                           !
 10293)    !  16    : rank 2 : polygon, dbh                                                        !
 10294)    !  17    : rank 2 : polygon, age                                                        !
 10295)    !  18    : rank 2 : polygon, mort                                                       !
 10296)    !  19    : rank 2 : polygon, month+1                                                    !
 10297)    !                                                                                       !
 10298)    !  20    : rank 1 : site, integer                                                       !
 10299)    !  21    : rank 1 : site                                                                !
 10300)    !  22    : rank 2 : site, s-layer                                                       !
 10301)    !  23    : rank 2 : site, w-layer                                                       !
 10302)    !  24    : rank 2 : site, pft                                                           !
 10303)    !  246   : rank 3 : site, pft, dbh                                                      !
 10304)    !  25    : rank 2 : site, disturbance                                                   !
 10305)    !  255   : rank 3 : site, disturbance, disturbance                                      !
 10306)    !  26    : rank 2 : site, dbh                                                           !
 10307)    !  27    : rank 2 : site, age                                                           !
 10308)    !  28    : rank 2 : site, mort                                                          !
 10309)    !  29    : rank 2 : site, month                                                         !
 10310)    !                                                                                       !
 10311)    !  30    : rank 1 : patch, integer                                                      !
 10312)    !  31    : rank 1 : patch                                                               !
 10313)    ! -31    : rank 2 : patch, diurnal cycle                                                !
 10314)    !  32    : rank 2 : patch, s-layer                                                      !
 10315)    !  33    : rank 2 : patch, w-layer                                                      !
 10316)    !  34    : rank 2 : patch, pft                                                          !
 10317)    !  346   : rank 3 : patch, pft, ff_dbh                                                  !
 10318)    !  35    : rank 2 : patch, disturbance                                                  !
 10319)    !  36    : rank 2 : patch, dbh                                                          !
 10320)    !  37    : rank 2 : patch, age                                                          !
 10321)    !  38    : rank 2 : patch, mort                                                         !
 10322)    !                                                                                       !
 10323)    !  40    : rank 1 : cohort, integer                                                     !
 10324)    !  41    : rank 1 : cohort                                                              !
 10325)    ! -41    : rank 2 : cohort, diurnal cycle                                               !
 10326)    !  44    : rank 2 : cohort, pft                                                         !
 10327)    !  46    : rank 2 : cohort, dbh                                                         !
 10328)    !  47    : rank 2 : cohort, age                                                         !
 10329)    !  48    : rank 2 : cohort, mort                                                        !
 10330)    !  49    : rank 2 : cohort, month+1                                                     !
 10331)    !  411   : rank 2 : cohort, radiation                                                   !
 10332)    ! -411   : rank 2 : cohort, diurnal cycle , radiation                                   !
 10333)    !  90    : rank 0 : integer scalar                                                      !
 10334)    !  92    : rank 1 : s-layer                                                             !
 10335)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10336)    subroutine filltab_alltypes
 10337) 
 10338)       use ed_var_tables, only : num_var                  & ! intent(in)
 10339)                               , vt_info                  & ! intent(inout)
 10340)                               , var_table                & ! intent(inout)
 10341)                               , reset_vt_vector_pointers ! ! sub-routine
 10342)       use ed_node_coms , only : mynum                    & ! intent(in)
 10343)                               , nnodetot                 ! ! intent(in)
 10344)       use ed_max_dims  , only : maxgrds                  & ! intent(in)
 10345)                               , maxmach                  ! ! intent(in)
 10346)       implicit none
 10347) 
 10348) #if defined(RAMS_MPI)
 10349)       include 'mpif.h'
 10350) #endif
 10351)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10352)       type(edtype)                                 , pointer   :: cgrid
 10353)       type(polygontype)                            , pointer   :: cpoly
 10354)       type(sitetype)                               , pointer   :: csite
 10355)       type(patchtype)                              , pointer   :: cpatch
 10356)       integer                                                  :: ncohorts_g
 10357)       integer                                                  :: npatches_g
 10358)       integer                                                  :: nsites_g
 10359)       integer                                                  :: igr
 10360)       integer                                                  :: ipy
 10361)       integer                                                  :: isi
 10362)       integer                                                  :: ipa
 10363)       integer                                                  :: nv
 10364)       integer                                                  :: nm
 10365) #if defined(RAMS_MPI)
 10366)       integer          , dimension(MPI_STATUS_SIZE)            :: status
 10367) #endif
 10368)       !----- Local constants. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10369)       logical                                      , parameter :: verbose = .false.    
 10370)       !----- Local saved variables. -------------------------------------------------------!
 10371)       logical                                      , save      :: model_start = .true.
 10372)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10373) 
 10374) 
 10375)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10376)       if (mynum == 1 .and. verbose) then
 10377)          write(unit=*,fmt='(a)') '--- Re-hashing the IO pointer tables and mapping arrays'
 10378)       end if
 10379)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10380) 
 10381) 
 10382) 
 10383)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10384)       !      The first loop through populates the info tables.                             !
 10385)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10386)       do igr = 1,ngrids
 10387)          cgrid => edgrid_g(igr)
 10388)          if (num_var(igr) > 0) then
 10389)             do nv=1,num_var(igr)
 10390)                call reset_vt_vector_pointers(vt_info(nv,igr))
 10391)             end do
 10392)          end if
 10393) 
 10394)          num_var(igr)           = 0
 10395) 
 10396)          cgrid%npolygons_global = cgrid%npolygons
 10397)          cgrid%nsites_global    = get_nsites(cgrid)
 10398)          cgrid%npatches_global  = get_npatches(cgrid)
 10399)          cgrid%ncohorts_global  = get_ncohorts(cgrid)
 10400)          
 10401)          cgrid%mach_cohort_offset_index = 0
 10402)          cgrid%mach_patch_offset_index  = 0
 10403)          cgrid%mach_site_offset_index   = 0
 10404)          cgrid%mach_polygon_offset_index= 0
 10405) 
 10406)          if (nnodetot /= 1) then
 10407) 
 10408)             !----- Send all them sizes to root (CHANGED, NODE 1). -------------------------!
 10409)             if (mynum == 1) then
 10410)             
 10411)                gdpy(1,igr) = cgrid%npolygons_global
 10412)                gdsi(1,igr) = cgrid%nsites_global
 10413)                gdpa(1,igr) = cgrid%npatches_global
 10414)                gdco(1,igr) = cgrid%ncohorts_global
 10415) 
 10416) #if defined(RAMS_MPI)
 10417)                call MPI_Send(ping,1,MPI_INTEGER,sendnum,94,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10418)                
 10419)                !----- Have node 1 recieve the info. ---------------------------------------!
 10420)                do nm=2,nnodetot
 10421)                   uniqueid = ((igr-1)*maxmach)+nm
 10422)                   call MPI_Recv(gdpy(nm,igr),1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                       &
 10423)                                ,500000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10424)                   call MPI_Recv(gdsi(nm,igr),1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                       &
 10425)                                ,600000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10426)                   call MPI_Recv(gdpa(nm,igr),1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                       &
 10427)                                ,700000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10428)                   call MPI_Recv(gdco(nm,igr),1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                       &
 10429)                                ,800000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10430)                end do
 10431)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10432) 
 10433) 
 10434) 
 10435)                !----- Broadcast all this info to the nodes. -------------------------------!
 10436)                do nm=2,nnodetot
 10437)                   uniqueid=((igr-1)*maxmach)+nm
 10438)                   call MPI_Send(gdpy,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                 &
 10439)                                , 900000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10440)                   call MPI_Send(gdsi,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                 &
 10441)                                ,1000000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10442)                   call MPI_Send(gdpa,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                 &
 10443)                                ,1100000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10444)                   call MPI_Send(gdco,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(nm)                 &
 10445)                                ,1200000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10446)                end do
 10447)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10448) #endif
 10449)             else
 10450) 
 10451) #if defined(RAMS_MPI)
 10452)                !----- Set the blocking receive to allow ordering, start with machine 1. ---!
 10453)                call MPI_Recv(ping,1,MPI_INTEGER,recvnum,94,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10454)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10455) 
 10456)                uniqueid=((igr-1)*maxmach)+mynum
 10457)                !----- Send the information to node (1). -----------------------------------!
 10458)                call MPI_Send(cgrid%npolygons_global, 1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                &
 10459)                             ,500000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10460)                call MPI_Send(cgrid%nsites_global   , 1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                &
 10461)                             ,600000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10462)                call MPI_Send(cgrid%npatches_global , 1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                &
 10463)                             ,700000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10464)                call MPI_Send(cgrid%ncohorts_global , 1,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                &
 10465)                             ,800000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10466) 
 10467)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10468)                !     When this node is finished, send the blocking MPI_Send to the next    !
 10469)                ! machine.                                                                  !
 10470)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10471)                if (mynum /= nnodetot) call MPI_Send(ping,1,MPI_INTEGER,sendnum             &
 10472)                                                    ,94,MPI_COMM_WORLD,ierr)
 10473)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10474) 
 10475) 
 10476)                !------ Receive the data from the main node. -------------------------------!
 10477)                uniqueid=((igr-1)*maxmach)+mynum
 10478)                call MPI_Recv(gdpy,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                     &
 10479)                             , 900000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10480)                call MPI_Recv(gdsi,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                     &
 10481)                             ,1000000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10482)                call MPI_Recv(gdpa,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                     &
 10483)                             ,1100000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10484)                call MPI_Recv(gdco,maxmach*maxgrds,MPI_INTEGER,machs(1)                     &
 10485)                             ,1200000+uniqueid,MPI_COMM_WORLD,status,ierr)
 10486)                !---------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10487) #else
 10488)                continue
 10489) #endif
 10490)             end if
 10491)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10492) 
 10493) 
 10494)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10495)             !     Display the information.                                                 !
 10496)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10497)             if (mynum == 1 .and. model_start .and. verbose) then
 10498)                
 10499)                print*,"Global Polygons: ",gdpy(1:nnodetot,igr)
 10500)                print*,"Global Site: "    ,gdsi(1:nnodetot,igr)
 10501)                print*,"Global Patches: " ,gdpa(1:nnodetot,igr)
 10502)                print*,"Global Cohorts: " ,gdco(1:nnodetot,igr)
 10503)             end if
 10504)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10505) 
 10506) 
 10507) 
 10508) 
 10509)             !----- Calculate the offsets that each machine has. ---------------------------!
 10510)             py_off(1,igr) = 0
 10511)             si_off(1,igr) = 0
 10512)             pa_off(1,igr) = 0
 10513)             co_off(1,igr) = 0
 10514)             do nm=2,nnodetot
 10515)                py_off(nm,igr) = py_off(nm-1,igr) + gdpy(nm-1,igr)
 10516)                si_off(nm,igr) = si_off(nm-1,igr) + gdsi(nm-1,igr)
 10517)                pa_off(nm,igr) = pa_off(nm-1,igr) + gdpa(nm-1,igr)
 10518)                co_off(nm,igr) = co_off(nm-1,igr) + gdco(nm-1,igr)
 10519)             end do
 10520)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10521) 
 10522) 
 10523)             !----- Calculate the total sizes of the arrays. -------------------------------!
 10524)             cgrid%npolygons_global = sum(gdpy(1:nnodetot,igr))
 10525)             cgrid%nsites_global    = sum(gdsi(1:nnodetot,igr))
 10526)             cgrid%npatches_global  = sum(gdpa(1:nnodetot,igr))
 10527)             cgrid%ncohorts_global  = sum(gdco(1:nnodetot,igr))
 10528)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10529) 
 10530) 
 10531) 
 10532)             !----- Calculate the local offsets. -------------------------------------------!
 10533)             cgrid%mach_polygon_offset_index = py_off(mynum,igr)
 10534)             cgrid%mach_site_offset_index    = si_off(mynum,igr)
 10535)             cgrid%mach_patch_offset_index   = pa_off(mynum,igr)
 10536)             cgrid%mach_cohort_offset_index  = co_off(mynum,igr)
 10537)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10538)          end if
 10539)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10540) 
 10541) 
 10542) 
 10543) 
 10544)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10545)          !      Call the routines that will fill the variable table for the first time.    !
 10546)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10547)          call filltab_globtype(igr)
 10548)          call filltab_edtype(igr,0)
 10549)          if (gdpy(mynum,igr) > 0) then
 10550)             call filltab_polygontype(igr,1,0)
 10551)             call filltab_sitetype   (igr,1,1,0)
 10552)             call filltab_patchtype  (igr,1,1,1,0)
 10553)          end if
 10554)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10555)       end do
 10556)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10557) 
 10558) 
 10559)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10560)       !     Loop over all grids again.                                                     !
 10561)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10562)       do igr = 1,ngrids
 10563)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10564)          !    Test to see if the var_table has been initialized.  If it has, then          !
 10565)          ! de-allocate its pointers and reset its first flag.  These will be reallocated   !
 10566)          ! on the first pass of the filltab_ subroutines.                                  !
 10567)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10568)          cgrid => edgrid_g(igr)
 10569) 
 10570)          !----- Find the global index. ----------------------------------------------------!
 10571)          cgrid%pyglob_id = 0 + cgrid%mach_polygon_offset_index
 10572)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10573) 
 10574) 
 10575)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10576)          !      Determine the total number of variables for each grid.  These will         !
 10577)          ! determine the length of the vt_vector.                                          !
 10578)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10579)          call filltab_edtype(igr,1)
 10580)          !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10581) 
 10582)          ncohorts_g = 0 + cgrid%mach_cohort_offset_index
 10583)          npatches_g = 0 + cgrid%mach_patch_offset_index
 10584)          nsites_g   = 0 + cgrid%mach_site_offset_index
 10585) 
 10586) 
 10587)          do ipy = 1,cgrid%npolygons
 10588)             cpoly => cgrid%polygon(ipy)
 10589)             !----- This is the offset for the vtable write. -------------------------------!
 10590)             cpoly%siglob_id = nsites_g + 0
 10591)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10592) 
 10593)             !----- This is the index written in the file for the user to reference. -------!
 10594)             cgrid%pysi_id(ipy) = nsites_g + 1 ! 
 10595)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10596) 
 10597) 
 10598)             !----- This is the dimension of the sites that belong to this polygon. --------!
 10599)             cgrid%pysi_n(ipy) = cpoly%nsites
 10600)             !------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10601) 
 10602)             nsites_g = nsites_g + cpoly%nsites
 10603)             call filltab_polygontype(igr,ipy,1)
 10604) 
 10605)             do isi = 1,cpoly%nsites
 10606)                csite => cpoly%site(isi)
 10607) 
 10608)                csite%paglob_id    = npatches_g + 0
 10609)                cpoly%sipa_id(isi) = npatches_g + 1
 10610)                cpoly%sipa_n(isi)  = csite%npatches
 10611)                npatches_g         = npatches_g + csite%npatches
 10612)                call filltab_sitetype(igr,ipy,isi,1)
 10613) 
 10614)                do ipa = 1,csite%npatches
 10615)                   cpatch => csite%patch(ipa)
 10616) 
 10617)                   cpatch%coglob_id   = ncohorts_g + 0
 10618)                   csite%paco_id(ipa) = ncohorts_g + 1
 10619)                   csite%paco_n(ipa)  = cpatch%ncohorts
 10620)                   ncohorts_g         = ncohorts_g + cpatch%ncohorts
 10621) 
 10622)                   if (cpatch%ncohorts > 0) then
 10623)                      call filltab_patchtype(igr,ipy,isi,ipa,1)
 10624)                   end if
 10625)                end do
 10626)             end do
 10627)          end do
 10628)          if (mynum == 1 .and. verbose) then
 10629)             write(*,"(a)")'--- Mapping Completed'
 10630)          end if
 10631) 
 10632)          if (mynum == 1 .and. model_start .and. verbose) then
 10633)             model_start = .false.
 10634)             do nv=1,num_var(igr)
 10635)                write(unit=*,fmt='(a,i4,a,i4,a,a)') 'Registering: ',nv,' of',num_var(igr)   &
 10636)                                                              ,'  ',vt_info(nv,igr)%name
 10637)             end do
 10638)          end if 
 10639)       end do
 10640) 
 10641) 
 10642)       return
 10643)    end subroutine filltab_alltypes
 10644)    !=======================================================================================!
 10645)    !=======================================================================================!
 10646) 
 10647) 
 10648) 
 10649) 
 10650) 
 10651) 
 10652)    !=======================================================================================!
 10653)    !=======================================================================================!
 10654)    subroutine filltab_globtype(igr)
 10655) 
 10656)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r       & ! sub-routine
 10657)                               , vtable_edio_r_sca   & ! sub-rouitne
 10658)                               , vtable_edio_i_sca   ! ! sub-rouitne
 10659)       use soil_coms    , only : slz                 & ! intent(in)
 10660)                               , slxclay             & ! intent(in)
 10661)                               , slxsand             & ! intent(in)
 10662)                               , isoilflg            ! ! intent(in)
 10663) 
 10664) 
 10665)       implicit none
 10666)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10667)       integer     , intent(in) :: igr
 10668)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10669)       integer                  :: var_len
 10670)       integer                  :: max_ptrs
 10671)       integer                  :: var_len_global
 10672)       integer                  :: nvar
 10673)       type(edtype), pointer    :: cgrid
 10674)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10675) 
 10676) 
 10677)       cgrid => edgrid_g(igr)
 10678) 
 10679) 
 10680)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10681)       !     Single values (scalars).                                                       !
 10682)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10683)       var_len        = 1
 10684)       var_len_global = 1
 10685)       max_ptrs       = 1
 10686) 
 10687)       nvar=1
 10688)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%npolygons_global,nvar,igr,0,0                           &
 10689)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10690)                             ,'NPOLYGONS_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10691)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%npolygons_global,nvar,igr,1,0                           &
 10692)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10693)                             ,'NPOLYGONS_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10694)       
 10695)       nvar=nvar+1
 10696)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%nsites_global,nvar,igr,0,0                              &
 10697)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10698)                             ,'NSITES_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10699)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%nsites_global,nvar,igr,1,0                              &
 10700)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10701)                             ,'NSITES_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10702)       
 10703)       nvar=nvar+1
 10704)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%npatches_global,nvar,igr,0,0                            &
 10705)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10706)                             ,'NPATCHES_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10707)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%npatches_global,nvar,igr,1,0                            &
 10708)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10709)                             ,'NPATCHES_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10710) 
 10711)       nvar=nvar+1
 10712)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(cgrid%ncohorts_global,nvar,igr,0,0                            &
 10713)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &

 10717)                             ,'NCOHORTS_GLOBAL :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')

 10722)                             ,'NZG :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')

 10724)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &

 10732)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10733)                             ,'NZS :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10734)

 10736)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(ff_nhgt,nvar,igr,0,0                                              &
 10737)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10738)                             ,'FF_NHGT :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')

 10740)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10741)                             ,'FF_NHGT :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')

 10746)                             ,'NDCYCLE :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10747)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(ndcycle,nvar,igr,1,0                                              &
 10748)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10749)                             ,'NDCYCLE :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10750) 
 10751)       nvar=nvar+1
 10752)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(isoilflg(igr),nvar,igr,0,0                                    &
 10753)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10754)                             ,'ISOILFLG :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10755)       call vtable_edio_i_sca(isoilflg(igr),nvar,igr,1,0                                    &
 10756)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10757)                             ,'ISOILFLG :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10758) 
 10759)       nvar=nvar+1
 10760)       call vtable_edio_r_sca(slxsand,nvar,igr,0,0                                          &
 10761)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10762)                             ,'SLXSAND :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10763)       call vtable_edio_r_sca(slxsand,nvar,igr,1,0                                          &
 10764)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10765)                             ,'SLXSAND :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10766) 
 10767)       nvar=nvar+1
 10768)       call vtable_edio_r_sca(slxclay,nvar,igr,0,0                                          &
 10769)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10770)                             ,'SLXCLAY :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')

 10772)                             ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                               &
 10773)                             ,'SLXCLAY :90:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10774) 
 10775)

 10778)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!

 10780)       var_len_global = nzg
 10781) 
 10782) 
 10783)

 10786)                         ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                   &
 10787)                         ,'SLZ :92:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10788)       call vtable_edio_r(nzg,slz,nvar,igr,1,0                                              &
 10789)                         ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                   &
 10790)                         ,'SLZ :92:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10791)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10792) 
 10793) 
 10794)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10795)       !    1-D variables, height classes.                                                  !
 10796)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10797)       var_len        = ff_nhgt
 10798)       var_len_global = ff_nhgt
 10799) 
 10800) 
 10801) 
 10802)       nvar=nvar+1
 10803)       call vtable_edio_r(ff_nhgt,hgt_class,nvar,igr,0,0                                    &
 10804)                         ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                   &
 10805)                         ,'HGT_CLASS :96:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10806)       call vtable_edio_r(ff_nhgt,hgt_class,nvar,igr,1,0                                    &
 10807)                         ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                   &
 10808)                         ,'HGT_CLASS :96:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10809)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10810) 
 10811) 
 10812)    
 10813) 
 10814) 
 10815)       !----- Save the number of global-level variables that go to the output. -------------!
 10816)       nioglobal=nvar
 10817)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10818) 
 10819)       return
 10820)    end subroutine filltab_globtype
 10821)    !=======================================================================================!
 10822)    !=======================================================================================!
 10823) 
 10824)

 10827) 
 10828) 
 10829)    !=======================================================================================!
 10830)    !=======================================================================================!
 10831)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 10832)    ! (edtype).                                                                             !
 10833)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10834)    subroutine filltab_edtype(igr,init)
 10835) 
 10836)       implicit none
 10837)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10838)       integer     , intent(in) :: init
 10839)       integer     , intent(in) :: igr
 10840)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10841)       type(edtype), pointer    :: cgrid
 10842)       integer                  :: var_len
 10843)       integer                  :: max_ptrs
 10844)       integer                  :: var_len_global
 10845)       integer                  :: nvar
 10846)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10847) 
 10848)       cgrid => edgrid_g(igr)
 10849) 
 10850)       !------ Define the global dimensions. -----------------------------------------------!
 10851)       var_len        = cgrid%npolygons
 10852)       var_len_global = cgrid%npolygons_global
 10853)       max_ptrs       = 1
 10854) 
 10855)       !------ Continue the counting. ------------------------------------------------------!
 10856)       nvar = nioglobal
 10857) 
 10858)       call filltab_edtype_p10     (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10859)       call filltab_edtype_p11inst (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10860)       call filltab_edtype_p11fmean(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10861)       call filltab_edtype_p11dmean(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10862)       call filltab_edtype_p11mmean(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10863)       call filltab_edtype_m11     (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10864)       call filltab_edtype_p12     (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10865)       call filltab_edtype_m12     (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10866)       call filltab_edtype_p19     (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10867)       call filltab_edtype_p146    (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10868)       call filltab_edtype_p199    (cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10869)       !----- Save the number of polygon-level (edtype) variables that go to the output. ---!
 10870)       if (init == 0) niogrid=nvar-nioglobal
 10871)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10872) 
 10873)       return
 10874)      
 10875)    end subroutine filltab_edtype
 10876)    !=======================================================================================!
 10877)    !=======================================================================================!
 10878) 
 10879) 
 10880) 
 10881)

 10884)    !=======================================================================================!
 10885)    !=======================================================================================!
 10886)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 10887)    ! (edtype) that have one dimension and are integer (type 10).                           !
 10888)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10889)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p10(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10890)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_i  & ! sub-routine
 10891)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 10892) 
 10893)       implicit none
 10894)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10895)       type(edtype), target        :: cgrid
 10896)       integer     , intent(in)    :: init
 10897)       integer     , intent(in)    :: igr
 10898)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len
 10899)       integer     , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 10900)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 10901)       integer     , intent(inout) :: nvar
 10902)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10903)       integer                     :: npts
 10904)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10905)       
 10906)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10907)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10908)       !     This is the 1-D block.  All variables must have the number of points defined   !
 10909)       ! by npts.                                                                           !
 10910)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10911) 
 10912)       npts = cgrid%npolygons
 10913) 
 10914)       if (associated(cgrid%pysi_id)) then
 10915)          nvar = nvar + 1
 10916)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cgrid%pysi_id,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id               &
 10917)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 10918)                            ,'PYSI_ID :10:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10919)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygons first site indices','[--]','(ipoly)')
 10920)       end if
 10921) 
 10922)       
 10923)       if (associated(cgrid%pysi_n)) then
 10924)          nvar=nvar+1
 10925)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cgrid%pysi_n,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                &
 10926)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 10927)                            ,'PYSI_N :10:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 10928)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Number of sites per polygon','[--]','(ipoly)')
 10929)       end if
 10930) 
 10931)       if (associated(cgrid%xatm)) then
 10932)          nvar=nvar+1
 10933)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cgrid%xatm,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                  &
 10934)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 10935)                            ,'XATM :10:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 10936)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Atm. cell x-indices of polygon','NA','ipoly')
 10937)       end if
 10938)       
 10939)       if (associated(cgrid%yatm)) then
 10940)          nvar=nvar+1
 10941)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cgrid%yatm,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                  &
 10942)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 10943)                            ,'YATM :10:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 10944)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Atm cell y-indices of polygon','NA','ipoly')
 10945)       end if
 10946)       
 10947)       if (associated(cgrid%load_adjacency)) then
 10948)          nvar=nvar+1
 10949)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cgrid%load_adjacency,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 10950)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'LOAD_ADJACENCY :10:hist') 
 10951)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Load Adjacency','[NA]','ipoly')
 10952)       end if
 10953)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10954) 
 10955)       return
 10956)    end subroutine filltab_edtype_p10
 10957)    !=======================================================================================!
 10958)    !=======================================================================================!
 10959) 
 10960) 
 10961)
