 10965)    !=======================================================================================!
 10966)    !=======================================================================================!
 10967)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 10968)    ! (edtype) that have one dimension and are real (type 11), and are instantaneous.       !
 10969)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10970)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p11inst(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 10971)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 10972)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 10973) 
 10974)       implicit none
 10975)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10976)       type(edtype), target        :: cgrid
 10977)       integer     , intent(in)    :: init
 10978)       integer     , intent(in)    :: igr
 10979)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len
 10980)       integer     , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 10981)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 10982)       integer     , intent(inout) :: nvar
 10983)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 10984)       integer                     :: npts
 10985)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10986) 
 10987) 
 10988)       
 10989)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10990)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10991)       !     This is the 1-D block.  All variables must have the number of points defined   !
 10992)       ! by npts.                                                                           !
 10993)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 10994)       npts = cgrid%npolygons
 10995) 
 10996)       if (associated(cgrid%lon)) then
 10997)          nvar=nvar+1
 10998)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%lon,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                   &
 10999)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 11000)                            ,'LONGITUDE :11:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 11001)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Longitude of Polygon','[deg]','(ipoly)')
 11002)       end if
 11003) 
 11004)       if (associated(cgrid%lat)) then
 11005)          nvar=nvar+1
 11006)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%lat,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                   &
 11007)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 11008)                            ,'LATITUDE :11:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year')
 11009)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Latitude of Polygon','[deg]','(ipoly)')
 11010)       end if
 11011) 
 11012)       
 11013)       if (associated(cgrid%wbar)) then
 11014)          nvar=nvar+1
 11015)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%wbar,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id                  &
 11016)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs                                &
 11017)                            ,'WBAR :11:hist') 
 11018)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 11019)                            ,'Polygon average topographic moisture index'                   &
 11020)                            ,'NA','(ipoly)')
 11021)       end if
 11022)       
 11023)       if (associated(cgrid%Te)) then
 11024)          nvar=nvar+1
 11025)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%Te                                                  &
 11026)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11027)                            ,'TE :11:hist') 
 11028)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','NA','(ipoly)')
 11029)       end if
 11030)       
 11031)       if (associated(cgrid%zbar)) then
 11032)          nvar=nvar+1
 11033)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%zbar                                                &
 11034)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11035)                            ,'ZBAR :11:hist:anal:opti') 
 11036)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon average water table depth','[m]','(ipoly)')
 11037)       end if
 11038)       
 11039)       if (associated(cgrid%sheat)) then
 11040)          nvar=nvar+1
 11041)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%sheat                                               &
 11042)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11043)                            ,'SHEAT :11:hist') 
 11044)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Soil heat pool for lateral hydrology','NA','(ipoly)')
 11045)       end if
 11046)       
 11047)       if (associated(cgrid%baseflow)) then
 11048)          nvar=nvar+1
 11049)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%baseflow                                            &
 11050)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11051)                            ,'BASEFLOW :11:hist:anal:opti') 
 11052)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 11053)                            ,'Loss of water from site to watershed discharge'               &
 11054)                            ,'[kg/m2/s]','(ipoly)')
 11055)       end if
 11056)       
 11057)       if (associated(cgrid%runoff)) then
 11058)          nvar=nvar+1
 11059)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%runoff                                              &
 11060)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11061)                            ,'RUNOFF :11:hist:anal:opti') 
 11062)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'NA','NA','ipoly')
 11063)       end if
 11064)       
 11065)       if (associated(cgrid%qrunoff)) then
 11066)          nvar=nvar+1
 11067)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qrunoff                                             &
 11068)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11069)                            ,'QRUNOFF :11:hist:anal:opti') 
 11070)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'NA','NA','ipoly')
 11071)       end if
 11072)       
 11073)       if (associated(cgrid%swliq)) then
 11074)          nvar=nvar+1
 11075)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%swliq,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 11076)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'SWLIQ :11:hist:anal') 
 11077)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'NA','NA','ipoly')
 11078)       end if
 11079) 
 11080)       if (associated(cgrid%total_agb)) then
 11081)          nvar=nvar+1
 11082)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%total_agb,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 11083)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'TOTAL_AGB :11:hist:anal:year:opti') 
 11084)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon Total Above Ground Biomass','[kgC/m2]','ipoly')
 11085)       end if
 11086)       
 11087)       if (associated(cgrid%total_basal_area)) then
 11088)          nvar=nvar+1
 11089)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%total_basal_area,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 11090)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'TOTAL_BASAL_AREA :11:hist:anal:year') 
 11091)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon Total Basal Area','[cm2/m2]','ipoly')
 11092)          
 11093)       end if
 11094) 
 11095)       if (associated(cgrid%total_agb_growth)) then
 11096)          nvar=nvar+1
 11097)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%total_agb_growth,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 11098)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'TOTAL_AGB_GROWTH:11:hist:anal:year') 
 11099)           call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon AGB gain through growth','[kgC/m2/yr]','ipoly')
 11100)       end if
 11101)       
 11102)       if (associated(cgrid%total_agb_mort)) then
 11103)          nvar=nvar+1
 11104)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%total_agb_mort,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id, &
 11105)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'TOTAL_AGB_MORT :11:hist:anal:year') 
 11106)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon AGB lost due to mortality','[kgC/m2/yr]','ipoly')

 11397)    !=======================================================================================!
 11398)    !=======================================================================================!
 11399) 
 11400) 
 11401) 
 11402) 
 11403) 
 11404) 
 11405)    !=======================================================================================!
 11406)    !=======================================================================================!
 11407)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 11408)    ! (edtype) that have one dimension and are real (type 11), and are fast mean variables. !
 11409)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11410)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p11fmean(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 11411)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 11412)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 11413) 
 11414)       implicit none
 11415)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11416)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 11417)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 11418)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 11419)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 11420)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 11421)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 11422)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 11423)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 11424)       integer                               :: npts
 11425)       character(len=str_len)                :: fast_keys
 11426)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11427) 
 11428) 
 11429) 
 11430)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11431)       !      Decide whether to write the sub-daily means to the history file.              !
 11432)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11433)       if (history_fast) then
 11434)          fast_keys = 'hist:anal:opti'
 11435)       else
 11436)          fast_keys = 'anal:opti'
 11437)       end if
 11438)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11439) 
 11440) 
 11441)       
 11442)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11443)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11444)       !     This is the 1-D block.  All variables must have the number of points defined   !
 11445)       ! by npts.                                                                           !
 11446)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 11447)       npts = cgrid%npolygons
 11448) 
 11449)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_gpp             )) then
 11450)          nvar = nvar+1
 11451)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_gpp                                           &
 11452)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11453)                            ,'FMEAN_GPP_PY               :11:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 11454)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 11455)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Gross primary productivity'                  &
 11456)                            ,'[  kgC/m2/yr]','(ipoly)'            )
 11457)       end if
 11458)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_npp             )) then
 11459)          nvar = nvar+1
 11460)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_npp                                           &
 11461)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 11462)                            ,'FMEAN_NPP_PY               :11:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 11463)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 11464)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Net primary productivity'                    &
 11465)                            ,'[  kgC/m2/yr]','(ipoly)'            )
 11466)       end if
 11467)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_leaf_resp       )) then
 11468)          nvar = nvar+1

 13840)    !=======================================================================================!
 13841)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 13842)    ! (edtype) that have one dimension and are real (type 11), and are monthly mean         !
 13843)    ! variables.                                                                            !
 13844)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13845)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p11mmean(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 13846)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 13847)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 13848) 
 13849)       implicit none
 13850)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13851)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 13852)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 13853)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 13854)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 13855)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 13856)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 13857)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 13858)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 13859)       integer                               :: npts
 13860)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 13861)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13862) 
 13863) 
 13864) 
 13865)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13866)       !      Check whether we need to save monthly means to history or not.                !
 13867)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13868)       if (history_eorq) then
 13869)          eorq_keys = 'hist:mont:dcyc'
 13870)       else
 13871)          eorq_keys = 'mont:dcyc'
 13872)       end if
 13873)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13874) 
 13875) 
 13876) 
 13877)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13878)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13879)       !     This is the 1-D block.  All variables must have the number of points defined   !
 13880)       ! by npts.                                                                           !
 13881)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 13882)       npts = cgrid%npolygons
 13883) 
 13884)       if (associated(cgrid%mmean_gpp             )) then

 13888)                            ,'MMEAN_GPP_PY               :11:'//trim(eorq_keys))
 13889)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 13890)                            ,'Monthly mean - Gross primary productivity'                    &
 13891)                            ,'[  kgC/m2/yr]','(ipoly)'            )
 13892)       end if

 13899)                            ,'Monthly mean - Net primary productivity'                      &

 13906)                            ,'MMEAN_LEAF_RESP_PY         :11:'//trim(eorq_keys))
 13907)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 13908)                            ,'Monthly mean - Leaf respiration'                              &
 13909)                            ,'[  kgC/m2/yr]','(ipoly)'            )
 13910)       end if
 13911)       if (associated(cgrid%mmean_root_resp       )) then
 13912)          nvar = nvar+1

 13914)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 13915)                            ,'MMEAN_ROOT_RESP_PY         :11:'//trim(eorq_keys))
 13916)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 13917)                            ,'Monthly mean - Root respiration'                              &
 13918)                            ,'[  kgC/m2/yr]','(ipoly)'            )

 13922)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%mmean_leaf_growth_resp                              &

 13938)       if (associated(cgrid%mmean_sapa_growth_resp)) then

 13944)                            ,'Monthly mean - Aboveground sapwood growth respiration'        &

 15366)    !=======================================================================================!
 15367)    !=======================================================================================!
 15368) 
 15369) 
 15370) 
 15371) 
 15372) 
 15373) 
 15374)    !=======================================================================================!
 15375)    !=======================================================================================!
 15376)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 15377)    ! (edtype) that have two dimensions (ndcycle,npolygons) and are real (type -11).        !
 15378)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15379)    subroutine filltab_edtype_m11(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 15380)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 15381)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 15382) 
 15383)       implicit none
 15384)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15385)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 15386)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 15387)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 15388)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 15389)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 15390)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 15391)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 15392)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 15393)       integer                               :: npts
 15394)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 15395)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15396) 
 15397) 
 15398)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15399)       !     Decide whether to save the mean diel variables to history or not.              !
 15400)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15401)       if (history_eorq) then
 15402)          eorq_keys = 'hist:dcyc'
 15403)       else
 15404)          eorq_keys = 'dcyc'
 15405)       end if
 15406)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15407) 
 15408) 
 15409)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15410)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 15411)       !     This is the 2-D block, with diurnal cycle.  All variables must have the number !
 15412)       ! of points defined by npts.                                                         !
 15413)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!

 16726)    !=======================================================================================!
 16727)    !=======================================================================================!
 16728) 
 16729) 
 16730) 
 16731) 
 16732) 
 16733) 
 16734)    !=======================================================================================!
 16735)    !=======================================================================================!
 16736)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 16737)    ! (edtype) that have two dimensions (ndcycle,npolygons) and are real (type 12).         !
 16738)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16739)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p12(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 16740)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 16741)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 16742) 
 16743)       implicit none
 16744)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16745)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 16746)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 16747)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 16748)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 16749)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 16750)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 16751)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 16752)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 16753)       integer                               :: npts
 16754)       character(len=str_len)                :: fast_keys
 16755)       character(len=str_len)                :: dail_keys
 16756)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 16757)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16758) 
 16759) 
 16760) 
 16761)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16762)       !      Decide whether to write fast, daily, and monthly mean variables to history.   !
 16763)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16764)       if (history_fast) then
 16765)          fast_keys = 'hist:anal:opti'
 16766)       else
 16767)          fast_keys = 'anal:opti'
 16768)       end if
 16769)       if (history_dail) then
 16770)          dail_keys = 'hist:dail'
 16771)       else
 16772)          dail_keys = 'dail'
 16773)       end if
 16774)       if (history_eorq) then
 16775)          eorq_keys = 'hist:mont:dcyc'
 16776)       else
 16777)          eorq_keys = 'mont:dcyc'
 16778)       end if
 16779)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16780) 
 16781) 
 16782) 
 16783) 
 16784)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16785)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16786)       !     This is the 2-D block, with soil layers.  All variables must have the number   !
 16787)       ! of points defined by npts.                                                         !
 16788)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 16789)       npts = cgrid%npolygons * nzg
 16790)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_soil_energy     )) then
 16791)          nvar = nvar+1
 16792)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_soil_energy                                   &
 16793)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 16794)                            ,'FMEAN_SOIL_ENERGY_PY       :12:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 16795)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 16796)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Soil internal energy'                        &
 16797)                            ,'[       J/m3]','(nzg,ipoly)'        )
 16798)       end if
 16799)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_soil_mstpot     )) then
 16800)          nvar = nvar+1
 16801)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_soil_mstpot                                   &
 16802)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 16803)                            ,'FMEAN_SOIL_MSTPOT_PY       :12:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 16804)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 16805)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Soil matric potential'                       &
 16806)                            ,'[          m]','(nzg,ipoly)'        )
 16807)       end if
 16808)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_soil_water      )) then
 16809)          nvar = nvar+1
 16810)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_soil_water                                    &
 16811)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 16812)                            ,'FMEAN_SOIL_WATER_PY        :12:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 16813)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 16814)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Soil water content'                          &
 16815)                            ,'[      m3/m3]','(nzg,ipoly)'        )
 16816)       end if
 16817)       if (associated(cgrid%fmean_soil_temp       )) then
 16818)          nvar = nvar+1
 16819)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%fmean_soil_temp                                     &
 16820)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 16821)                            ,'FMEAN_SOIL_TEMP_PY         :12:'//trim(fast_keys)     )
 16822)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 16823)                            ,'Sub-daily mean - Soil temperature'                            &
 16824)                            ,'[          K]','(nzg,ipoly)'        )
 16825)       end if

 17022)    !=======================================================================================!
 17023)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 17024)    ! (edtype) that have three dimensions (nzg,ndcycle,npolygons) and are real (type -12).  !
 17025)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17026)    subroutine filltab_edtype_m12(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17027)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 17028)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 17029) 
 17030)       implicit none
 17031)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17032)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 17033)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 17034)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 17035)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 17036)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 17037)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 17038)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 17039)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 17040)       integer                               :: npts
 17041)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 17042)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17043) 
 17044) 
 17045) 
 17046) 
 17047)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17048)       !      Decide whether to write the mean diel variables to the history.               !
 17049)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17050)       if (history_eorq) then
 17051)          eorq_keys = 'hist:dcyc'
 17052)       else
 17053)          eorq_keys = 'dcyc'
 17054)       end if
 17055)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17056) 
 17057) 
 17058) 
 17059) 
 17060)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17061)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17062)       !     This is the 3-D block, with soil depth class and diurnal cycle.  All vari-     !
 17063)       ! ables must have the number of points defined by npts.                              !
 17064)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17065)       npts = cgrid%npolygons *  nzg * ndcycle
 17066)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_soil_energy     )) then
 17067)          nvar = nvar+1
 17068)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_soil_energy                                   &
 17069)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17070)                            ,'QMEAN_SOIL_ENERGY_PY      :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17071)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17072)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil internal energy'                             &
 17073)                            ,'[       J/m3]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17074)       end if
 17075)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_soil_mstpot     )) then
 17076)          nvar = nvar+1
 17077)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_soil_mstpot                                   &
 17078)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17079)                            ,'QMEAN_SOIL_MSTPOT_PY      :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17080)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17081)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil matric potential'                            &
 17082)                            ,'[          m]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17083)       end if
 17084)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_soil_water      )) then
 17085)          nvar = nvar+1
 17086)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_soil_water                                    &
 17087)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17088)                            ,'QMEAN_SOIL_WATER_PY       :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17089)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17090)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil water content'                               &
 17091)                            ,'[      m3/m3]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17092)       end if
 17093)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_soil_temp       )) then
 17094)          nvar = nvar+1
 17095)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_soil_temp                                     &
 17096)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17097)                            ,'QMEAN_SOIL_TEMP_PY        :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17098)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17099)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil temperature'                                 &
 17100)                            ,'[          K]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17101)       end if
 17102)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_soil_fliq       )) then
 17103)          nvar = nvar+1
 17104)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_soil_fliq                                     &
 17105)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17106)                            ,'QMEAN_SOIL_FLIQ_PY        :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17107)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17108)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil liquid fraction'                             &
 17109)                            ,'[         --]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17110)       end if
 17111)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_smoist_gg       )) then
 17112)          nvar = nvar+1
 17113)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_smoist_gg                                     &
 17114)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17115)                            ,'QMEAN_SMOIST_GG_PY        :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17116)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17117)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil water flux'                                  &
 17118)                            ,'[    kg/m2/s]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17119)       end if
 17120)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_transloss       )) then
 17121)          nvar = nvar+1
 17122)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_transloss                                     &
 17123)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17124)                            ,'QMEAN_TRANSLOSS_PY        :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17125)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17126)                            ,'Mean diel - Water loss through transpiration'                 &
 17127)                            ,'[    kg/m2/s]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17128)       end if
 17129)       if (associated(cgrid%qmean_sensible_gg     )) then
 17130)          nvar = nvar+1
 17131)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%qmean_sensible_gg                                   &
 17132)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17133)                            ,'QMEAN_SENSIBLE_GG_PY      :-12:'//trim(eorq_keys)     )
 17134)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr                                                       &
 17135)                            ,'Mean diel - Soil heat flux'                                   &
 17136)                            ,'[       W/m2]','(nzg,ndcycle,ipoly)')
 17137)       end if
 17138)       return     
 17139)    end subroutine filltab_edtype_m12

 17148)    !=======================================================================================!
 17149)    !=======================================================================================!
 17150)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 17151)    ! (edtype) that have two dimensions (13 months,npolygons) and are real (type 19).       !
 17152)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17153)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p19(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17154)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 17155)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 17156) 
 17157)       implicit none
 17158)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17159)       type(edtype), target        :: cgrid
 17160)       integer     , intent(in)    :: init
 17161)       integer     , intent(in)    :: igr
 17162)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len
 17163)       integer     , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 17164)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 17165)       integer     , intent(inout) :: nvar
 17166)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 17167)       integer                     :: npts
 17168)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17169) 
 17170)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17171)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17172)       !     This is the 2-D block, with 13 months.  All variables must have the            !
 17173)       ! number of points defined by npts.                                                  !
 17174)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17175)       npts = cgrid%npolygons * 13
 17176) 
 17177)       if(associated(cgrid%workload)) then
 17178)          nvar=nvar+1
 17179)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%workload                                            &
 17180)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 17181)                            ,'WORKLOAD :19:hist:mont:dcyc') 
 17182)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon computational workload'                      &
 17183)                            ,'[steps/month]','(13,ipoly)') 
 17184)       end if
 17185)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17186)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17187) 
 17188) 
 17189)       return     
 17190)    end subroutine filltab_edtype_p19
 17191)    !=======================================================================================!
 17192)    !=======================================================================================!
 17193) 
 17194) 
 17195) 
 17196) 
 17197) 
 17198) 
 17199)    !=======================================================================================!
 17200)    !=======================================================================================!
 17201)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 17202)    ! (edtype) that have three dimensions (n_dbh,n_pft,npolygons) and are real (type 146).  !
 17203)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17204)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p146(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17205)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 17206)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 17207) 
 17208)       implicit none
 17209)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17210)       type(edtype)          , target        :: cgrid
 17211)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 17212)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 17213)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 17214)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 17215)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 17216)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 17217)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 17218)       integer                               :: npts
 17219)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 17220)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17221) 
 17222) 
 17223) 
 17224)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17225)       !     Decide whether to write monthly means to history or not.                       !
 17226)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17227)       if (history_eorq) then
 17228)          eorq_keys = 'hist:mont:dcyc'
 17229)       else
 17230)          eorq_keys = 'mont:dcyc'
 17231)       end if
 17232)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17233) 
 17234)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17235)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17236)       !     This is the 3-D block, with PFT and size class.  All variables must have the   !
 17237)       ! number of points defined by npts.                                                  !
 17238)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17239)       npts = cgrid%npolygons * n_pft * n_dbh

 17526)    !=======================================================================================!
 17527)    !=======================================================================================!
 17528)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the polygon-level variables         !
 17529)    ! (edtype) that have three dimensions (3,4,npolygons) and are real (type 199).          !
 17530)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17531)    subroutine filltab_edtype_p199(cgrid,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17532)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 17533)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 17534) 
 17535)       implicit none
 17536)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17537)       type(edtype), target        :: cgrid
 17538)       integer     , intent(in)    :: init
 17539)       integer     , intent(in)    :: igr
 17540)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len
 17541)       integer     , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 17542)       integer     , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 17543)       integer     , intent(inout) :: nvar
 17544)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 17545)       integer                     :: npts
 17546)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17547) 
 17548) 
 17549)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17550)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17551)       !     This is the 3-D block, with LAI and 4 vars.  All variables must have the       !
 17552)       ! number of points defined by npts.                                                  !
 17553)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17554)       npts = cgrid%npolygons * 3 * 4
 17555) 
 17556)       if (associated(cgrid%avg_lai_ebalvars)) then
 17557)          nvar=nvar+1
 17558)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cgrid%avg_lai_ebalvars                                  &
 17559)                           ,nvar,igr,init,cgrid%pyglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs &
 17560)                            ,'AVG_LAI_EBALVARS :199:anal') 
 17561)         call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Polygon Average Energy Balance Variables'           &
 17562)                           ,'[variable]','(4,3,ipoly)') 
 17563)       end if
 17564)       
 17565)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17566)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17567) 
 17568) 
 17569) 
 17570)       return     
 17571)    end subroutine filltab_edtype_p199
 17572)    !=======================================================================================!
 17573)    !=======================================================================================!
 17574) 
 17575) 
 17576) 
 17577) 
 17578) 
 17579) 
 17580)    !=======================================================================================!
 17581)    !=======================================================================================!
 17582)    !     This sub-routine fills in the variable table with site-level variables.           !
 17583)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17584)    subroutine filltab_polygontype(igr,ipy,init)
 17585)       implicit none
 17586)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17587)       integer, intent(in) :: init
 17588)       integer, intent(in) :: igr
 17589)       integer, intent(in) :: ipy
 17590)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 17591)       type(polygontype), pointer :: cpoly
 17592)       integer                    :: var_len
 17593)       integer                    :: max_ptrs
 17594)       integer                    :: var_len_global
 17595)       integer                    :: nvar
 17596)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17597) 
 17598) 
 17599) 
 17600)       !----- Check whether this polygon is allocated. -------------------------------------!
 17601)       if (.not.associated(edgrid_g(igr)%polygon(ipy)%sipa_id)) then
 17602)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       '------------------------------------------------'
 17603)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       ' Returning from filltab_polygontype'
 17604)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i5)') ' IGR  = ',igr
 17605)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i5)') ' IPY  = ',ipy
 17606)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a,1x,i5)') ' INIT = ',init
 17607)          write (unit=*,fmt='(a)')       '------------------------------------------------'
 17608)          return
 17609)       end if
 17610)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17611) 
 17612) 
 17613) 
 17614)       !----- Assign a pointer to the current polygon. -------------------------------------!
 17615)       cpoly => edgrid_g(igr)%polygon(ipy)
 17616)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17617) 
 17618) 
 17619) 
 17620)       !----- Define some variables to be used by all variables. ---------------------------!
 17621)       var_len        = cpoly%nsites
 17622)       var_len_global = edgrid_g(igr)%nsites_global
 17623)       max_ptrs       = edgrid_g(igr)%npolygons
 17624)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17625) 
 17626) 
 17627)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17628)       !     Initialise the variable number, which should be unique for each variable.      !
 17629)       ! nioglobal has the current position after all the parent structure variables have   !
 17630)       ! been positioned in the variable table.                                             !
 17631)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17632)       nvar=nioglobal+niogrid
 17633)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17634) 
 17635) 
 17636) 
 17637)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17638)       !      We split the routine into smaller ones to avoid excessive number of calls to  !
 17639)       ! sub-routines from the same routine (this allows more optimisation for ifort, and   !
 17640)       ! reduces chances of segmentation violation during the compilation).                 !
 17641)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17642)       call filltab_polygontype_p20     (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17643)       call filltab_polygontype_p21inst (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17644)       call filltab_polygontype_p21fmean(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17645)       call filltab_polygontype_p21dmean(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17646)       call filltab_polygontype_p21mmean(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17647)       call filltab_polygontype_p220    (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17648)       call filltab_polygontype_p24     (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17649)       call filltab_polygontype_m21     (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17650)       call filltab_polygontype_p29     (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17651)       call filltab_polygontype_p246    (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17652)       call filltab_polygontype_p255    (cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 17653)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17654) 
 17655) 
 17656)       !----- Save the number of site-level (polygontype) variables that go to the output. -!
 17657)       if (init == 0) niopoly=nvar-niogrid-nioglobal
 17658)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 17659) 
 17660)       return
 17661)    end subroutine filltab_polygontype

 18053)       !      Decide whether to write the sub-daily means to the history file.              !

 18064)       end select

 18459)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18460)       !      Decide whether to write the monthly means to the history file.                !

 18653)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the site-level variables            !
 18654)    ! (polygontype) that have two dimensions (nzg,nsites) and are integer (type 220).       !
 18655)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18656)    subroutine filltab_polygontype_p220(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 18657)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_i  & ! sub-routine
 18658)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 18659) 
 18660)       implicit none
 18661)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18662)       type(polygontype), target        :: cpoly
 18663)       integer          , intent(in)    :: init
 18664)       integer          , intent(in)    :: igr
 18665)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len
 18666)       integer          , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 18667)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 18668)       integer          , intent(inout) :: nvar
 18669)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 18670)       integer                          :: npts
 18671)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18672) 
 18673) 
 18674) 
 18675) 
 18676) 
 18677)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18678)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18679)       !     This is the 2-D block, with dimensions being nsites and nzg.  Make sure to     !
 18680)       ! include only variables of types 22 and 220 here, as they will all use the same     !
 18681)       ! npts.                                                                              !
 18682)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18683)       npts = cpoly%nsites * nzg
 18684) 
 18685)   
 18686)       if (associated(cpoly%ntext_soil)) then
 18687)          nvar=nvar+1
 18688)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,cpoly%ntext_soil                                          &
 18689)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cpoly%siglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 18690)                            ,'NTEXT_SOIL :220:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 18691)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Soil texture class','[--]','(isite)')
 18692)       end if
 18693) 
 18694)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18695)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18696) 
 18697)       return
 18698)    end subroutine filltab_polygontype_p220

 18984)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the site-level variables            !
 18985)    ! (polygontype) that have two dimensions (12 months,nsites) and are real (type 29).     !
 18986)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18987)    subroutine filltab_polygontype_p29(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 18988)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 18989)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 18990) 
 18991)       implicit none
 18992)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 18993)       type(polygontype), target        :: cpoly
 18994)       integer          , intent(in)    :: init
 18995)       integer          , intent(in)    :: igr
 18996)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len
 18997)       integer          , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 18998)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 18999)       integer          , intent(inout) :: nvar
 19000)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 19001)       integer                          :: npts
 19002)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19003) 
 19004) 
 19005) 
 19006) 
 19007) 
 19008) 
 19009)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19010)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19011)       !     This is the 2-D block, with dimensions being nsites and 12 months.  Make sure  !
 19012)       ! to include only variables of type 29 here, as they will all use the same npts.     !
 19013)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19014)       npts = cpoly%nsites * 12
 19015) 
 19016)       if (associated(cpoly%lambda_fire)) then
 19017)          nvar=nvar+1
 19018)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cpoly%lambda_fire,nvar,igr,init,cpoly%siglob_id           &
 19019)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'LAMBDA_FIRE :29:hist')
 19020)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19021)       end if
 19022) 
 19023)       if (associated(cpoly%avg_monthly_pcpg)) then
 19024)          nvar=nvar+1
 19025)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cpoly%avg_monthly_pcpg,nvar,igr,init,cpoly%siglob_id      &
 19026)                            ,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'AVG_MONTHLY_PCPG :29:hist')     
 19027)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19028)       end if
 19029)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19030)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19031)       return
 19032)    end subroutine filltab_polygontype_p29

 19095)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA')

 19152)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the site-level variables            !
 19153)    ! (polygontype) that have three dimensions (n_dist_types,n_dist_types,nsites) and are   !
 19154)    ! real (type 255).                                                                      !
 19155)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19156)    subroutine filltab_polygontype_p255(cpoly,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19157)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 19158)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 19159) 
 19160)       implicit none
 19161)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19162)       type(polygontype), target        :: cpoly
 19163)       integer          , intent(in)    :: init
 19164)       integer          , intent(in)    :: igr
 19165)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len
 19166)       integer          , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 19167)       integer          , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 19168)       integer          , intent(inout) :: nvar
 19169)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 19170)       integer                          :: npts
 19171)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19172) 
 19173) 
 19174) 
 19175) 
 19176) 
 19177)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19178)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19179)       !     This is the 3-D block, with dimensions being nsites and n_dist_types,          !
 19180)       ! n_dist_types (from and to).  Make sure to include only variables of type 255 here, !
 19181)       ! as they will all use the same npts.                                                !

 19190)       end if
 19191)

 19194)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,cpoly%disturbance_rates                                   &
 19195)                            ,nvar,igr,init,cpoly%siglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &

 19213)    !=======================================================================================!
 19214)    !=======================================================================================!
 19215)    !     This sub-routine will fill the variable table with the sitetype variables (patch- !
 19216)    ! -level).  Because of the sheer number of variables, we must split the subroutines     !
 19217)    ! into smaller routines.                                                                !
 19218)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19219)    subroutine filltab_sitetype(igr,ipy,isi,init)
 19220) 
 19221)       implicit none
 19222)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19223)       integer       , intent(in) :: init
 19224)       integer       , intent(in) :: igr
 19225)       integer       , intent(in) :: ipy
 19226)       integer       , intent(in) :: isi
 19227)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 19228)       type(sitetype), pointer    :: csite
 19229)       integer                    :: var_len
 19230)       integer                    :: max_ptrs
 19231)       integer                    :: var_len_global
 19232)       integer                    :: nvar
 19233)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19234) 
 19235) 
 19236) 
 19237)       !----- Assign a pointer to the current polygon. -------------------------------------!
 19238)       csite => edgrid_g(igr)%polygon(ipy)%site(isi)
 19239)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19240) 
 19241) 
 19242) 
 19243)       !----- Define some variables to be used by all variables. ---------------------------!
 19244)       var_len        = csite%npatches
 19245)       var_len_global = edgrid_g(igr)%npatches_global
 19246)       max_ptrs       = get_nsites(edgrid_g(igr))
 19247)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19248) 
 19249) 
 19250)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19251)       !     Initialise the variable number, which should be unique for each variable.      !
 19252)       ! nioglobal has the current position after all the parent structure variables have   !
 19253)       ! been positioned in the variable table.                                             !
 19254)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19255)       nvar=nioglobal+niogrid+niopoly
 19256)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19257) 
 19258)       call filltab_sitetype_p30     (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19259)       call filltab_sitetype_p31inst (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19260)       call filltab_sitetype_p31fmean(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19261)       call filltab_sitetype_p31dmean(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19262)       call filltab_sitetype_p31mmean(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19263)       call filltab_sitetype_m31     (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19264)       call filltab_sitetype_p32     (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19265)       call filltab_sitetype_p33     (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19266)       call filltab_sitetype_p34     (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19267)       call filltab_sitetype_p346    (csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19268)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19269) 
 19270)       !----- Save the number of patch-level (sitetype) variables that go to the output. ---!
 19271)       if (init == 0) niosite=nvar-niopoly-niogrid-nioglobal
 19272)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19273) 
 19274)       return
 19275)    end subroutine filltab_sitetype
 19276)    !=======================================================================================!
 19277)    !=======================================================================================!
 19278) 
 19279) 
 19280) 
 19281) 
 19282)

 19284)    !=======================================================================================!
 19285)    !=======================================================================================!
 19286)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the patch-level variables           !
 19287)    !  (sitetype) that have one dimension and are integer (type 30).                        !
 19288)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19289)    subroutine filltab_sitetype_p30(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 19290)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_i  & ! sub-routine
 19291)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 19292) 
 19293)       implicit none
 19294)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19295)       type(sitetype), target        :: csite
 19296)       integer       , intent(in)    :: init
 19297)       integer       , intent(in)    :: igr
 19298)       integer       , intent(in)    :: var_len
 19299)       integer       , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 19300)       integer       , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 19301)       integer       , intent(inout) :: nvar
 19302)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 19303)       integer                       :: npts
 19304)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19305) 
 19306) 
 19307) 
 19308) 
 19309)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19310)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19311)       !       This part should have only 1-D vectors (npatches).  Notice that they all use !
 19312)       ! npts = csite%npatches.  Add only variables of type 30.                             !
 19313)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19314)       npts = csite%npatches
 19315) 
 19316) 
 19317)       if (associated(csite%paco_id)) then
 19318)          nvar=nvar+1
 19319)          call vtable_edio_i(npts,csite%paco_id,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id, &
 19320)               var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'PACO_ID :30:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 19321)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19322)       end if
 19323) 
 19324)       if (associated(csite%paco_n)) then
 19325)          nvar=nvar+1
 19326)            call vtable_edio_i(npts,csite%paco_n,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id, &
 19327)            var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'PACO_N :30:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 19328)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19329)       end if
 19330)       
 19331)       if (associated(csite%dist_type)) then
 19332)          nvar=nvar+1
 19333)            call vtable_edio_i(npts,csite%dist_type,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id, &
 19334)            var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'DIST_TYPE :30:hist:anal:dail:mont:dcyc:year') 
 19335)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19336)       end if
 19337) 
 19338)       if (associated(csite%nlev_sfcwater)) then
 19339)          nvar=nvar+1
 19340)            call vtable_edio_i(npts,csite%nlev_sfcwater,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id, &
 19341)            var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,'NLEV_SFCWATER :30:hist:year') 
 19342)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'No metadata available','[NA]','NA') 
 19343)       end if
 19344)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 19345) 
 19346)       return
 19347)    end subroutine filltab_sitetype_p30

 20705)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine

 21250)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the patch-level variables           !
 21251)    ! (sitetype) that have one dimension, are real (type 31), and are monthly means or mean !
 21252)    ! sum of squares.                                                                       !
 21253)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21254)    subroutine filltab_sitetype_p31mmean(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 21255)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 21256)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 21257) 
 21258)       implicit none
 21259)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21260)       type(sitetype)        , target        :: csite
 21261)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 21262)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 21263)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 21264)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 21265)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 21266)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 21267)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 21268)       integer                               :: npts
 21269)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 21270)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21271) 
 21272) 
 21273) 
 21274)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21275)       !      Decide whether to write the monthly means to the history file.                !
 21276)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21277)       select case (iadd_patch_means)
 21278)       case (0)
 21279)          return
 21280)       case (1)
 21281)          if (history_eorq) then
 21282)             eorq_keys = 'hist:mont:dcyc'

 21284)             eorq_keys = 'mont:dcyc'
 21285)          end if
 21286)       end select
 21287)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21288) 
 21289) 
 21290) 
 21291) 
 21292)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21293)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21294)       !       This part should have only 1-D vectors (npatches).  Notice that they all use !
 21295)       ! npts = csite%npatches.  Add only variables of type 31 that are monthly means.      !
 21296)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21297)       npts = csite%npatches

 21303)                            ,'MMEAN_RH_PA                :31:'//trim(eorq_keys))

 21975)          nvar = nvar+1

 21980)                            ,'Monthly MSSq - Sensible heat flux: atmosphere -> CAS'         &
 21981)                            ,'[      W2/m4]','(ipatch)'            )
 21982)       end if
 21983)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21984)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21985)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 21986) 
 21987)       return
 21988)    end subroutine filltab_sitetype_p31mmean

 21990)    !=======================================================================================!
 21991)

 21994) 
 21995) 
 21996) 
 21997)    !=======================================================================================!
 21998)    !=======================================================================================!
 21999)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the patch-level variables           !
 22000)    ! (sitetype) that have two dimensions (ndcycle,npatches), and are of type -31 (qmean    !
 22001)    ! and qmsqu).                                                                           !
 22002)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22003)    subroutine filltab_sitetype_m31(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 22004)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 22005)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 22006) 
 22007)       implicit none
 22008)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22009)       type(sitetype)        , target        :: csite
 22010)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init

 22016)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 22017)       integer                               :: npts
 22018)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 22019)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22020) 
 22021) 
 22022) 
 22023)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22024)       !      Decide whether to write the mean diel to the history file.                    !
 22025)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22026)       select case (iadd_patch_means)

 22037) 
 22038) 
 22039) 
 22040) 
 22041)

 22641)    !=======================================================================================!
 22642)    !=======================================================================================!
 22643) 
 22644) 
 22645) 
 22646) 
 22647) 
 22648) 
 22649)    !=======================================================================================!
 22650)    !=======================================================================================!
 22651)    !     This routine will fill the pointer table with the patch-level variables           !
 22652)    ! (sitetype) that have two dimensions (nzg,npatches).                                   !
 22653)    !---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22654)    subroutine filltab_sitetype_p32(csite,igr,init,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs,nvar)
 22655)       use ed_var_tables, only : vtable_edio_r  & ! sub-routine
 22656)                               , metadata_edio  ! ! sub-routine
 22657) 
 22658)       implicit none
 22659)       !----- Arguments. -------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22660)       type(sitetype)        , target        :: csite
 22661)       integer               , intent(in)    :: init
 22662)       integer               , intent(in)    :: igr
 22663)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len
 22664)       integer               , intent(in)    :: max_ptrs
 22665)       integer               , intent(in)    :: var_len_global
 22666)       integer               , intent(inout) :: nvar
 22667)       !----- Local variables. -------------------------------------------------------------!
 22668)       integer                               :: npts
 22669)       character(len=str_len)                :: fast_keys
 22670)       character(len=str_len)                :: dail_keys
 22671)       character(len=str_len)                :: eorq_keys
 22672)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22673) 
 22674) 
 22675) 
 22676) 
 22677)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22678)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22679)       !       This part should have only 2-D vectors with dimensions npatches and nzg.     !
 22680)       !  Notice that they all use the same npts.  Here you should only add variables of    !
 22681)       ! types 32 and 320.                                                                  !
 22682)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22683)       npts = csite%npatches * nzg
 22684) 
 22685)       if (associated(csite%soil_energy)) then
 22686)          nvar=nvar+1
 22687)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%soil_energy                                         &
 22688)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 22689)                            ,'SOIL_ENERGY_PA :32:hist') 
 22690)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Instantaneous - Soil internal energy'                &
 22691)                            ,'[J/m3]','(nzg,ipatch)') 
 22692)       end if
 22693) 
 22694)       if (associated(csite%soil_mstpot)) then
 22695)          nvar=nvar+1
 22696)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%soil_mstpot                                         &
 22697)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 22698)                            ,'SOIL_MSTPOT_PA :32:hist') 
 22699)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Instantaneous - Soil matric potential'               &
 22700)                            ,'[m]','(nzg,ipatch)') 
 22701)       end if
 22702) 
 22703)       if (associated(csite%soil_water)) then
 22704)          nvar=nvar+1
 22705)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%soil_water                                          &
 22706)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 22707)                            ,'SOIL_WATER_PA :32:hist')
 22708)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Soil moisture','[m3/m3]','(nzg,ipatch)') 
 22709)       end if
 22710) 
 22711)       if (associated(csite%soil_tempk)) then
 22712)          nvar=nvar+1
 22713)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%soil_tempk                                          &
 22714)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 22715)                            ,'SOIL_TEMPK_PA :32:hist') 
 22716)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Instantaneous - Soil temperature'                    &
 22717)                            ,'[K]','(nzg,ipatch)') 
 22718)       end if
 22719) 
 22720)       if (associated(csite%soil_fracliq)) then
 22721)          nvar=nvar+1
 22722)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%soil_fracliq                                        &
 22723)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &
 22724)                            ,'SOIL_FRACLIQ_PA :32:hist') 
 22725)          call metadata_edio(nvar,igr,'Instantaneous - Soil liquid water fraction'          &
 22726)                            ,'[--]','(nzg,ipatch)') 
 22727)       end if
 22728) 
 22729)       if (associated(csite%rootdense)) then
 22730)          nvar=nvar+1
 22731)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%rootdense                                           &
 22732)                            ,nvar,igr,init,csite%paglob_id,var_len,var_len_global,max_ptrs  &

 22738) 
 22739) 
 22740) 
 22741) 
 22742) 
 22743)

 22745)       !      Decide whether to write the fast, daily, and monthly means to the history.    !
 22746)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22747)       select case (iadd_patch_means)
 22748)       case (0)
 22749)          return
 22750)       case (1)
 22751)          if (history_fast) then
 22752)             fast_keys = 'hist:anal'
 22753)          else
 22754)             fast_keys = 'anal'
 22755)          end if
 22756)          if (history_dail) then
 22757)             dail_keys = 'hist:dail'
 22758)          else
 22759)             dail_keys = 'dail'
 22760)          end if
 22761)          if (history_eorq) then
 22762)             eorq_keys = 'hist:mont:dcyc'
 22763)          else
 22764)             eorq_keys = 'mont:dcyc'
 22765)          end if
 22766)       end select
 22767)       !------------------------------------------------------------------------------------!
 22768) 
 22769) 
 22770) 
 22771)       if (associated(csite%fmean_soil_energy     )) then
 22772)          nvar = nvar+1
 22773)          call vtable_edio_r(npts,csite%fmean_soil_energy                                   &
